title: eclair cake
directions: Layer 1/3 of the graham crackers in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine pudding mix and 3 cups milk in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer (about 2 minutes).
Fold in whipped topping; spoon half of the mixture on graham crackers. Repeat layers, ending with graham crackers.
You may not need all the crackers.
Combine sugar, butter and 1/3 cup milk in saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in morsels.
Spoon over crackers and top with pecans.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Combine sugars, margarine, pudding mix and vanilla in a large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Then stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen soft cookies.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Put chicken in casserole.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: tony's gumbo
directions: Boil and debone chicken (canned chicken meat and broth may be used).
Set aside.
In a large pot or skillet, heat oil and add flour to make roux.
Stir while browning until very brown, almost burned.
Add water and stir.
Add other ingredients.
Cover; let cook for 30 minutes on low to medium heat, stirring occasionally. Add more water, if needed.

title: ady's goodies
directions: Cook vanilla pudding and milk until thick.
Add 1 box German chocolate cake mix (dry).
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle 1 package chocolate chips and 1/2 to 1 cup chopped nuts over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken pieces generously.
Place flour in paper sack, then toss chicken pieces in flour sack.
Heat shortening and bacon drippings in heavy skillet (cast-iron is best) over medium-high heat until water drop sizzles.
Add chicken, being careful not to overcrowd.
Cook, covered, about 15 minutes or until brown creeps up the side of the chicken. Remove cover, turn chicken and continue to cook until browned, about 15 minutes. Drain, uncovered, on paper towels.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: banana orange drink
directions: Put contents into large mixing bowl and blend well for 2 minutes. Chill for 5 minutes. Pour into cups and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed on package.
Cut into small pieces.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise, soup and cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Roll crackers into crumbs, then mix with melted butter.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: smothered steak(dietetic)
directions: Brown steak in a nonstick pan.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, then on low for 8 hours. Yield: 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, pudding, oil and water.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar.
Serve it warm and the chocolate chips will still be melted.
It's delicious!

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil sugar and evaporated milk until forms soft ball.
Pour over other ingredients and beat.
Pour in greased pan or cookie sheet.
Allow to cool.
Makes about five pounds of candy. To keep, store in metal container and keep in cool place.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Combine cheese and sugar in large bowl; blend well.
Beat in cocoa, scraping sides of bowl and beaters.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add cream.
Blend well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (center will be soft).
Cool to room temperature. Chill for several hours.

title: toast
directions: Spread butter on bread and put on hot griddle about 1 minute on each side.
You may sprinkle cinnamon-sugar, if desired.

title: lemon-lime congealed salad
directions: Mix jello in hot water.
Add the mayonnaise while still hot. Mix the remaining ingredients and congeal.

title: red pop rhubarb jello
directions: Heat rhubarb and red pop until rhubarb is cooked.
Dissolve jello in cooked rhubarb and chill.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish in order as listed. Chill for 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: lemon lush
directions: Melt margarine; mix with flour and nuts.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: caramel peanut crunchies
directions: Place grahams in single layer on well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Sprinkle peanuts and chocolate chunks over crackers. Microwave caramels and milk in small bowl for 1 1/2 minutes. Stir. Microwave additional 1 1/2 minutes or until caramels are melted. Evenly drizzle over graham mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool completely. Cut into squares. Makes 24 squares.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine
beef,
green pepper and onion in large skillet; cook until brown.
Stir to crumble.
Add remaining ingredients. Put in lightly
greased
x
x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° about 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chili beef and biscuits
directions: Brown beef (pouring off fat) with chili powder, minced onion, green pepper and garlic powder.
Add tomato sauce; set aside. Line baking dish with 10 halves of a can of biscuits that have been split lengthwise.
Pour beef mixture over biscuits.
Top with other half of biscuits.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, melted butter and one egg.
Press into bottom of pan. Then mix pumpkin pie mix with 2 eggs and milk.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and drain.
Layer as listed, except mayonnaise, cheese and bacon.
Top with mayonnaise, cheese and crumbled bacon.

title: walnut tossed salad
directions: Cook and stir walnuts in oil in 8-inch skillet until toasted, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Remove walnuts with slotted spoon; drain.
Sprinkle with salt.
Stir vinegar and sugar into oil in skillet.
Pour over salad greens and onion; toss.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Makes 6 servings.
Each serving contains 165 calories.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sugar, egg yolk and flour in saucepan.
Cook until thick; cool about 2 hours.
Cook and cool macaroni as directed.
When sauce and macaroni have cooled, combine together and add all other ingredients.
May add coconut, if desired.

title: cherry blossom dessert
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking soda into mixing bowl.
Blend in brown sugar and oatmeal. Cut in the shortening until particles are the size of small peas.
Press 1/2 oatmeal mixture into bottom of ungreased 12 x 8 x 2 or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread with cherry pie filling. Add balance of oatmeal mixture on top.
Press gently with spoon.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until golden brown. Cut into squares.
Serve with cream, warm or cold.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Pound chicken breasts to flatten.
Combine mustard and wine in shallow dish; stir to blend.
In another shallow dish, combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Toss to mix. Lightly coat a baking sheet with nonstick vegetable spray.
Dip chicken into the mustard mixture, turning to coat both sides. Dredge chicken in crumbs to coat well.
Place on baking sheet. Coat all chicken breasts.
Bake 8 minutes.
If crumbs aren't brown enough, place under broiler for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then add 3 small jars strained carrot baby food.
Pour into greased cookie sheet or cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool and frost with your favorite frosting.

title: grasshopper
directions: Combine all these ingredients together in a blender; blend until smooth.
Enjoy on a hot summer day!

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix celery seed, salt, sugar, salad oil and white vinegar together.
Drain beans, except kidney beans.
Combine beans with onion and green pepper.
Pour dressing over and mix.
Chill.

title: pansit(philippine rice noodle)
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil.
Add chicken or preferred meat. Add soy sauce and oyster sauce, then vegies until crispy cooked (carrots, celery, cabbage, cilantro, snow peas).
Add rice noodles; mix and cook for 5 minutes or until done.
If juice is not enough to cook noodles, may add broth or water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain grease.
Add packets of seasoning.
Mix in tomato juice.
Mix in chili beans.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sugar made be added if desired.
Cook on medium heat.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Boil peanuts, Karo and sugar in microwave 4 minutes on High setting.
Remove and stir well.
Return to microwave and cook 4 more minutes on High.
Remove and add butter and vanilla.
Cook one more minute on High.
Remove and add baking soda.
Quickly pour on greased cookie sheet. Let cool until hardened.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together and put into a bag.
Put cut biscuits into the bag and shake to coat the pieces.
Put into stem pan.
Mix oleo and brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake.

title: white sugar cookies (with cream)
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add the beaten eggs and vanilla. Dissolve the soda in sour cream, then add to the creamed mixture. Stir in flour.
Roll out quite thin and bake in a moderate oven (375°).

title: strawberry punch
directions: Put strawberry Jell-O and sugar into 1 quart of hot water and dissolve.
Add pineapple juice, lemon juice and 1 quart of cold water.
Freeze.
Take out 2 hours before use and pour 1 quart of ginger ale over punch.

title: tropical ice(punch)
directions: Mix, then freeze all ingredients except the ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and mix well.
Yields 12 cups.

title: sour cream 'n sausages
directions: In glass casserole, mix together the soup, sour cream and mustard.
Stir in sausages; cover and cook or roast for 10 minutes or until hot, stirring once during cooking.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: swiss broccoli chowder
directions: Cook ham hocks in water 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender and falls off bone.
Drain, reserving 1 1/2 cups broth.
Let ham cool.
Dice and set aside.

title: meatball appetizers
directions: Combine ground chuck, egg, crumbs, onions, salt, pepper and oregano.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into 1-inch meatballs.
In skillet combine cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice. Simmer, stirring until sauce is smooth.
Add meatballs and simmer 1 hour.
Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
Mix next three ingredients and spread over the crust.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar, Karo and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: french bread
directions: Place warm water in a large mixing bowl; sprinkle yeast over water.
Add salt and 4 cups of flour; beat until well mixed.
Add enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured board and knead until smooth.
Place dough in bowl; cover with damp cloth.
Allow dough to almost triple (about 2 1/2 hours).
Punch dough down and then allow to rise another 40 minutes.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Using palms of hands, roll each part into a 15-inch long roll.
Sprinkle cornmeal on cookie sheet.
Place rolls of dough over cornmeal.
Make a 1/2-inch deep cut down the length of each roll.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Put part of apples in bottom of casserole dish and add 1 cup of sugar. Add the rest of the apples and 1 cup sugar.
Spread crumbs over mixture and pour melted butter on top.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Combine chicken, celery, onion, nuts, rice, chicken or mushroom soup, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Mix mayonnaise with water; add to chicken mixture. Gently stir in eggs.
Turn into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with potato chips and bake 10 more minutes.

title: banana custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt, nutmeg and milk.
Mash bananas; add custard mixture and lemon juice.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate and bake in hot 450° oven for first 10 minutes until firm, then reduce heat to moderate 325° temperature for 35 minutes longer.

title: freezer ice cream topping
directions: Stir all together.
Freeze in small jars.
Set out of freezer a couple of hours before using.
Delicious!

title: oven barbecued ribs
directions: Salt ribs; place in roasting pan, meaty side up.
Roast at 450° for 30 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Top each piece of rib with slice of onion.
Pour
barbecue
sauce over ribs.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 1
hours.
Baste
every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato and ham soup
directions: Boil potatoes and carrots in 6 cups water.
Simmer onion, celery and ham together for 15 minutes in 3 cups water and add 1/2 cup flour.
Drain potatoes and carrots; add additional 1/2 cup flour and 1 cup milk.
Stir until thickened.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put the cheese and butter in a food processor; blend until smooth.
Add flour and mix well.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut the dough into 2-inch squares and wrap a square around each olive, sealing the seams.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes.
Check after the first 10 minutes to see that Puffs don't burn.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain water off.
Add tuna, peas and celery soup.
Mix together.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken n' rice
directions: Place ingredients, one on top of the other, in order given in a large sheet cake pan.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 2 hours.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Mix cheese, milk, butter and garlic salt in saucepan over low heat until melted.
Add drained corn and peppers.
Bake in buttered casserole dish at 350° until heated through and bubbly. Yield: 10 servings.

title: crabmeat fondue(from 1975 edition)
directions: Melt the butter; saute the onions for a few minutes.
Add the cheese, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, sherry and seasonings.
Stir constantly until the mixture is smooth.
Add the prepared crabmeat and blend.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, salt and cornstarch in medium saucepan. Gradually blend milk into dry ingredients, stirring until smooth. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it boils; boil one minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter or margarine and vanilla.
Pour into cooled baked pie crust.
Quickly press plastic wrap directly onto pie filling; cool.
Chill 3 to 4 hours. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: cornbread cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hand or mixer.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake. When out of oven, cake will be soft.

title: yogi berry salad
directions: In a bowl, combine apple, grapes, strawberries, celery and raisins.
Toss gently.
Fold in yogurt.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, stir in sunflower seeds.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: meal-in-one casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Transfer to a slow cooker.
Top with the green pepper, corn and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with noodles.
Pour tomatoes and water over all. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook on low for 4 hrs or until noodles are tender.

title: cabbage stir-fry
directions: Heat
oil in wok or large frying pan.
Add cabbage and peppers.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes, lowering heat if cabbage begins to brown.
Stir in ginger root, sugar and salt. Add broth.
Cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes or until barely tender. Season with soy sauce.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: overnight chicken casserole(serves 8)
directions: Night Before:
In large bowl, combine milk, soup, uncooked cavatelli, peas, chicken, onion, cheese, 3 hard-cooked eggs (sliced) and the salt.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight, tightly covered.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Add first 6 ingredients together and cream.
Add the last 6 ingredients.
Put enough flour on table to roll out, if you like them rolled out, or put 1 teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Put on cookie rack to cool.

title: potato noodle soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions, carrots, garlic salt and celery seed until potatoes are done.
Add enough water to cook noodles.
When noodles are done, add bacon, parsley and milk.
Cook until steaming, then serve.
Season to taste.
Do not let soup boil after adding milk so it will not curdle.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef with cracker crumbs, egg, milk, onion and spices.
Pack lightly into casserole or loaf dish and cover with wax paper.
Cook 5 minutes on Medium-high, then top with ketchup. Cook 15 to 20 minutes more on Medium-high, rotating once.
Let sit 5 minutes before serving.

title: good cake
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, bake cake, according to directions. Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, combine pineapple with its juice and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick and syrupy, 20 minutes approximately.

title: french toast
directions: Mix egg, sugar and milk and dip slices of bread in.
Fry in pan.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add flour and salt, then vanilla and nuts.
Chill.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Do not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: viva la chicken
directions: Bake or boil chicken until done.
Debone and dice.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch strips.
Mix together soups, milk, broth, onion, salsa, chiles, olives and cheese. Reserve 3/4 of the cheese for topping.
In a
large oiled casserole dish, layer half of the ingredients starting with the tortillas, then chicken and finally sauce. Repeat, ending with the sauce.
Bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours. During the last 15 minutes of baking, top the dish with remaining 3/4 cup of cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked apple slices
directions: Peel and slice tart apples.
Place in flat Pyrex pan.
Boil the water, margarine and cinnamon for 2 minutes.
Pour over quartered apples; bake about 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: tea cakes(sugar cookies)
directions: Roll dough into balls.
Dip them in sugar (coat them well). Place on ungreased cookie sheet and pat flat.
Bake at 325°.

title: brownie pound cake
directions: Mix baking powder with water and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Sift together dry ingredients and add to cream mixture alternately with milk.
Beat in water and baking powder with flavoring last. Bake in greased and floured tube cake pan for 2 hours at 300°. This cake makes a crunchy top and will stay moist for days.

title: linguini salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate for at least 24 hours

title: chilly day soup
directions: Melt butter or oleo in a saucepan.
Add; cover and simmer for 20 minutes the onions and carrots.
Stir remaining ingredients in and heat to serving temperature.

title: chewy crumb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes on cookie sheet at 350°.

title: minnesota rhubarb shortcake
directions: Slice a layer of rhubarb 2 inches thick into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish and pour first 4 ingredients over it.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the first part.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Yummy!

title: veggie salad
directions: In saucepan melt butter and saute vegetables lightly-don't overcook.
Remove from heat and cool completely, transfer to bowl. Blend together oil and vinegar and pour over vegetables, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken for 1 hour or until tender.
Set aside to cool slightly.
In a medium saucepan, stir together the soup, milk and broth.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, if desired.
Break chicken into pieces and stir into soup mixture. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: medium white sauce
directions: In double boiler, melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk.
Bring to slightly boil, stirring constantly until thick.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients well except tortillas.
Spread thinly on the flour tortillas.
Roll like a jelly roll and refrigerate. When ready to serve, cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: poncet(filipino lo mein)
directions: Place meat into a large saucepan or wok after heating oil. Cook on medium heat until cooked through. Add flavor packets from the noodles with about 4 teaspoons soy sauce.

Add the vegetables and squirt lemon juice and more soy sauce onto the mixture. Continue stirring until all vegetables are cooked. Boil noodles and drain. Add noodles to meat and vegetables, along with 2 teaspoons lemon juice and soy sauce. Stir together until all noodles are covered with "sauce."
Place on a serving platter with wedges of lemon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Chop green part only of green onions; add to cream cheese.
Add seasoned salt, Worcestershire sauce and nuts and mix well.
Form into ball with wet hands.
Roll in meat mixture and serve with assorted crackers.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Cook pork roast in 1/2 cup water in crock-pot with cut up onion for 8 hours on low.
Cool.
Tear apart, discarding fat.
Shred and place back in crock-pot.
Add bottle of barbecue sauce.
Cook on low for 2 to 4 hours.
Serve over corn cakes or on buns.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir together.
Pour in glass 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover top with Cheese Nips and 1 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix the eggs, oil, extract and sour cream together and beat for 2 minutes in a large bowl.
Add cake mix and pie filling to mixture and beat at low speed for 30 seconds.
Scrape sides of bowl and beat on low for another 30 seconds.
Spread batter evenly in the bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes (until cake pulls away from the sides of the pan).
Cool on rack and serve chilled with whipped cream.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Melt butter and mix with 1/2 cup sugar and cracker crumbs. Line an 8-inch dish with half of the crumb mixture.

title: raspberry cake(fat-free)
directions: Mix gelatin according to package directions.
Using a bowl large enough to hold cake, stir in berries.
With gelatin in bottom of bowl, place cake in bowl, small end down (small plate and weight may be needed on top of cake to hold it down).
Chill until gelatin sets.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine apples, 1 cup sugar, salt, cinnamon, 1/3 cup flour and water; mix well.
Spoon apple mixture into pastry shell.
Combine remaining sugar and 1/2 cup flour; cut in margarine until crumbly. Spread crumbs over apple mixture.
Place pie in paper bag.
Fold ends of bag closed; fasten with paper clips.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: corned beef buns
directions: Mash corned beef; add sour cream and onion soup.
Put on buns.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put mix in a 3-quart casserole dish.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Power Select High. In 3-quart casserole dish, heat water and butter 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until boiling.
Stir in sugar and white syrup.
Heat 11 1/2 minutes (our microwave) or 13 to 14 minutes to 300° (but do not use thermometer while operating microwave). Quickly stir in peanuts and baking soda, stirring until soda foams.
Pour onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Spread thin.
Let stand until candy is hardened.
Break into small pieces.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add Coke.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, cherries, celery and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: del mexico potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Peel when cold; grate into long buttered casserole dish. Heat cheese, mustard, cream, milk, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour over potatoes. Dot with butter. Cool. Refrigerate 24 hours. Remove from refrigerator. Bake 1 hour on 325°.

title: yazoo salad
directions: Heat soup to warm.
Dissolve gelatin in water.
Pour into warmed soup.
Mix together with other ingredients and refrigerate. Serves 8.

title: date loaf
directions: Boil sugar and milk together. Cook until a soft ball stage. Just before time to take off, Add chopped dated. Take off heat. Add nuts and beat until stiff. Roll in a damp cloth. Allow to stand for a while, until firm. Cut in pieces.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat until warm enough to dissolve yeast. Add 3 cups flour; beat until gooey. On board, knead with lots of butter, but not stiff. Grease a large bowl with melted shortening. Put dough in bowl, coating it with shortening. Let rise until doubled. Knead small amount (about 1/3 of dough). Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness. Spread lots of butter, sugar and cinnamon over dough. Roll up and close ends. Cut 1 to 1 1/2-inches thick; close bottoms each time and flour. Put in greased pan. Top with small amount of melted shortening. Let rise until doubled. Bake at 350° until done. Put on bottom rack of oven for a few minutes so rolls will be browned on bottom.

title: pear cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture and then add in pears and pecans.
Grease and flour tube pan and bake at 350° for an hour.

title: great pasta
directions: Cook bacon in oil and butter (I omit both) along with pepper flakes.
When done to liking, drain pasta; toss bacon mixture, parsley and Romano with pasta.
Season to taste.
Enjoy!
Quick, easy and great.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add boiling water gradually.
Bring to boil; cook for 5 minutes.
Cool mixture.
Add fresh berries.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Top with whipped cream and whole berries.

title: barbara's chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute all vegetables in butter about 2 minutes.
Add flour, seasonings, water and tomato puree.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick.
Add shrimp; cook about 5 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy and add remaining ingredients. Beat until mixed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven in hot oil, brown roast on all sides. Spoon off fat. Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or tests done.
Remove roast and vegetables.
Stir together flour and remaining 1/4 cup water until smooth. Gradually stir into soup mixture. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken cheddar bake
directions: Boil chicken; when done, break into pieces.
Boil rice; drain, then place rice into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat cheese soup and add water until smooth.
Place chicken on top of rice in pan. Pour soup over chicken and rice in pan.
Break or crush cheese crackers and spread over top of cheese soup.
Bake at 375° approximately 45 minutes or until crackers brown, then eat and enjoy.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Drain orange slices and pineapple
tidbits. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Store in refrigerator.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Beat eggs; add cheese and milk.
Pour mixture in a frying pan with butter.
Cook slowly stirring constantly.
When mixture has consistency of scrambled eggs, serve over toast.
Serves 4.

title: crab bites
directions: Combine butter, cheese, mayonnaise, garlic and seasoned salt. Add
crabmeat
and	onion.	Spread	mixture
on English muffin halves.
Freeze until
solid.
Cut	into
pie shaped wedges. Each muffin half
yields
8 small pieces.
Heat under broiler until bubbly just before serving.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and soak overnight in lime water.
Wash and soak in salt water 4 hours, then wash and soak in clean water for 2 hours.
Drain and place in alum water and bring to a boil.
Dip in clear water again, then mix other ingredients and add to cucumbers.
Let simmer for 30 minutes and then place in jars and seal.

title: quick and easy brunswick stew
directions: Saute onion; add all other ingredients.
Stir well.
Heat to a good boil, stirring to keep from sticking.
If too thick, add some water, to keep from sticking.

title: hot toasted cheesies
directions: Mix together grated cheese, beaten egg, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Remove the crust from the bread. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Place a spoonful of mixture on a square. Toast in 450° oven until brown.

title: creole shrimp soup
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until shrimp are tender and rice is done, 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish with parsley.
Yields 8 servings.

title: never fail noodles
directions: Beat eggs and water until blended.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add to beaten eggs, a small amount at a time, until you have a very stiff dough.
Roll on a floured surface as thin as possible.
Cut noodles length desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peppered roast
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Spread pepper over beef and press in with palm of hand.
Marinate beef 24 hours in mixture of soy sauce, vinegar, catsup, paprika and garlic powder.
Remove from refrigerator.
Wrap beef in foil and place in pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours for well done until tender.
It is delicious hot or cold.

title: santa pack cookies
directions: Cut 2 slices of cookie dough (1/4-inch thick).
Cut one slice into 3 pieces.
Center piece should be a triangle.
Arrange pieces on cookie sheet.
Add chocolate chips for eyes and bake according to directions on the package.
Use the icing to add whiskers, hat, fur and tassel.
Red hots make a great nose and icing covered with red sprinkles create Santa's hat.

title: rice meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg, onions, salt, pepper, sugar and 1/2 cup tomato juice in bowl.
Form into balls and put in large skillet.
Add remaining tomato juice.
Cook over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes, turning once.

title: zucchini beef bake
directions: Spread zucchini evenly in a greased 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan; set aside.
Brown beef, onion and celery; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms, wine and seasonings.
Spoon over zucchini. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes until mixture bubbles and cheese is lightly browned.
Can be put together day before and refrigerated.
If so, bake a little longer and add cheese the last 10 minutes.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix chopped tomatoes, onions, sweet peppers and hot pepper. Let stand 2 hours in 1 cup salt.
Pour in colander and drain all night.
Mix sugar in vinegar and dissolve.
Add mustard seed and tomato mixture.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: spiced tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags, cloves and cinnamon.
Steep 10 to 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve. Makes about 5 quarts.
This stores well in refrigerator or may be frozen.

title: water whip pie crust
directions: Pour the Spry, boiling water and milk into a bowl and mix. Then beat until like whipped cream and holds peaks.
Stir in the flour and salt and mix until it makes a ball and cleans the sides of the bowl.
Pick up and work into a smooth ball.
Shape into a flat round.
The dough is ready to roll between waxed paper or on a floured board.
Enough for a 9-inch, 2-crust pie.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients.
Cut in shortening, then add egg and
milk
and
beat until smooth.
Let stand 10 minutes. Drop
by spoonful into boiling broth and cook 10 minutes.
No need to cover.

title: clara's dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in jars.
Add dill heads, garlic buttons and hot peppers.
Boil water with red vinegar and sack salt.
Pour mixture over cucumbers and seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, onion and celery.
Drain off water.
Add butter, rice, soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown ground beef and mix with soup mix, egg, soy sauce and pepper and spread on bread.
Spoon pizza sauce and cheese over each snack.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: carolyn's sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; cream until well blended. Sift flour, baking powder and salt to cream mixture and blend well.
Roll out on floured board and cut into desired shapes! Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes! Check often (as they do burn easily)!

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan, combine milk and soup.
Stir in broccoli, potatoes and onion.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
Add oil; mix well.
Add eggs; blend well.
Add carrots last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 4 ingredients.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except granulated sugar.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned popcorn balls
directions: Keep popped corn warm while making syrup.
Combine sugar, water, vinegar, corn syrup and salt in small deep pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, to very hard-ball stage (265° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Put 4 cups popped corn in a bowl.
Slowly pour over 1/2 the syrup mixture.
With fork quickly toss to coat kernels.
With buttered hands lightly press mixture into balls.
Reheat syrup before pouring over remaining corn.
Makes 8 to 12 popcorn balls.

title: cheese dressing
directions: Blend together sour cream and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Can be used over potato dishes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Spray Pam on 3-quart casserole dish.
Saute first 5 ingredients.
Add rice and remaining ingredients.
Mix well in mixing bowl.
Pour in casserole dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs. (Can be frozen at this stage.)
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. (Serves 8.)

title: caramel swirl buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (350° for colored pan).
Coat bottom and sides of a Bundt pan with 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine. Sprinkle pan with 1/3 of raisins and nuts (optional).
Melt remaining butter in a pan.
Add remaining raisins, nuts, sugar and water to melted butter.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Cut crescent rolls into 10 slices, separating the pinwheels so liquid can penetrate.
Spoon 1/2 of caramel sauce over dough. Repeat with second can of crescent rolls, placing the pinwheels over the first roll.
Pour remaining sauce over dough.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 3 minutes and turn over onto wax paper or plate.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix together and put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1 package of Ritz crackers (crushed) and 1 stick butter (melted). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and bacon
directions: Fry bacon; drain oil and smash to little pieces.
Cook noodles; drain water.
Mix together bacon, soup and noodles. Serve.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and let set in a cool place overnight.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with a cookie cutter and glaze with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together Miracle Whip salad dressing, vegetable oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour dressing mixture over potatoes, eggs and onion.
Mix well and put into serving bowl.
Top with 1 sliced egg.
Chill.

title: egg dip
directions: Mix together in bowl. Sprinkle top with paprika. Store covered in refrigerator until ready to serve with crackers.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Line pastry shell with the sausage.
Pour egg mixture over the sausage and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.

title: sweet pear loaf
directions: Beat oil and sugar together until well blended.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture. Beat until well blended. Add walnuts and pears; mix well.
Pour into well greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Let cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes; turn out on rack. Slice and enjoy.

title: sweet 'tater muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Lightly grease muffin pans. Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine milk, soup and pepper.
Place drained beans in a casserole dish.
Pour milk, soup and pepper over beans.
Add 1/2 of onions.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Top with remaining onions; bake for 5 more minutes.

title: sauce for grilled chicken(mild)
directions: Melt on stove to boiling point.
Brush on chicken a couple times.
May also be used as a marinade.

title: strawberry-pineapple salad
directions: In a bowl, combine cream cheese and honey. Blend well. Add strawberries and pineapple.
Blend well.
Pour into freezer tray. Freeze 2 hours.
Cut into 4 portions.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Garnish with sliced strawberries, if desired.

title: red flannel potato salad(serves 8)
directions: Drain beets, reserving juice.
Cut beet slices into quarters, set aside.
In large bowl, blend together 1/4 cup reserved beet juice, mayonnaise or oil, mustard and salt.
Toss lightly with remaining ingredients and reserved beets until evenly coated with dressing.
Cover and chill to blend flavors.
Garnish with additional egg slices, if desired.

title: groundnut chop-chicken in peanut butter sauce(west african recipe)
directions: Prepare chicken.
Melt oil in skillet; add peanut butter. Stir vigorously; add water and seasoning.
Stir in chicken and turn flame low.
Cover; stir from time to time and allow to cook for 6 to 7 minutes.
If more seasoning is desired, add when ready to serve.
Serve in a ring of flaky cooked rice with mango chutney, fresh coconut, fresh hot pepper and any other desired relish.

title: aunt patty's 24 hour salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 4 tablespoons syrup.
In top of a double boiler, beat egg yolks slightly.
Add the reserved syrup, sugar, vinegar, butter and a dash of salt.
Place over hot water; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly and barely coats on spoon, about 12 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in butter until tender.
Add soup and water. Cook until tender.
Stir milk and flour together.
Add to soup. Stir in cubed Velveeta cheese.
Cook until bubbly.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar, and cool whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Pour blueberries on top.
Chill.

title: mustardy sausage skillet
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cook in boiling, salted water until just cool enough to handle.
Peel.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
In a large frying pan, cook onion in heated butter until soft.
Add sausage slices.
Cook, stirring often, until lightly browned.
Mix in mustard, salt and cream.
Bring to boiling.
Lightly mix in tomatoes and potatoes. Cover.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are heated through, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice and cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion.
Cook rice.
Combine all and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Crush
graham
crackers.
Mix
sugar and baking powder. Add melted
margarine,	milk and eggs; mix well.
Add chopped cherries and pecans.
Bake in buttered and floured tube pan at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: puffed mashed potatoes
directions: Put in bowl and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add each ingredient into a large bowl and stir as you go. Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup sugar and butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese and pour over crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread; cool and crumble. Cook bacon until crisp and crumble. Mix chopped egg, onion, bell pepper, celery, mayonnaise and bacon with crumbled corn bread. Let stand for several hours. Just before serving, add chopped tomatoes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter,
sugar
and add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, soda, cream
of
tartar and salt together.
Mix in the evening and make into
long
rolls.
Cut in slices.
Bake in morning. Add nuts to half of batter if you like.
Can be rolled and use cookie cutters if you prefer.
Bake on 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mama's applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add applesauce and eggs. Sift all dry ingredients together and mix raisins and nuts. Add to first mixture. Pour into 4 (9-inch) greased and floured pans. Bake at 375° until tester comes out clean.

title: blanc mange
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a deep, 1-quart heat-resistant nonmetallic casserole.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Heat, uncovered, in microwave oven for 6 minutes, stirring every minute.
Allow to cook just until mixture begins to boil.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve topped with fresh fruit or whipped cream.

title: sue's brisket no. 1
directions: Mix all ingredients and rub into meat.
Seal in heavy foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake with fatty side up, still wrapped, for 6 hours at 250°.
Cool 1 hour before slicing.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Beat
eggs and add water and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients and combine with egg mixture with a few strokes.
Heat a 5-inch skillet
and
grease
with	a few drops of oil.
Add small	amount of
batter over bottom.
Brown on one side only and turn out on a plate, brown side up.
Fry all the blintzes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer and put into ice cream freezer.

title: baked trout
directions: Place trout into oblong pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, Old Bay and paprika.
Cover fish with plenty of chopped onion.
Place pats of butter all over fish.
Cover with foil and cook.
Cook at 350° until light brown.

title: microwave chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Mix tomato sauce and garlic in 2 cup measure.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir.
Reduce power to Medium; cook 5 minutes.
Mix corn flake crumbs, Parmesan and parsley.
Dip chicken in egg, then corn flake mixture.
Place in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook at Medium-high until chicken is tender (9 to 14 minutes).
Do not turn over.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle Mozzarella over chicken, then more Parmesan cheese.
Microwave on Medium-high until cheese melts, 2 to 5 1/2 minutes.

title: skillet beans 'n franks
directions: In skillet, melt butter; add tomato, oregano and garlic powder.
Cook a minute to blend flavors; add beans and franks. Heat,
stirring
often,
until mixture is piping hot.
Makes 6 servings.
Ready to serve in 5 to 10 minutes.

title: gorp or trail mix
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Store in glass jars.
(Use on camping trips or add 1/2 cup to cooked oatmeal for a hearty breakfast.)

title: tart 'n' saucy apple pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour.
Add lemon peel, lemon juice and applesauce and mix well. Add sliced apples.
Pour into bottom crust.
Dot with margarine.

title: apple dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
While cake is baking, prepare topping.

title: chicken casserole martin
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and stuffing.
Spread mixture in casserole dish.
Combine butter and stuffing; sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: cheery cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with pie filling.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Note:
There is no flour in this recipe.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour and stir until paste forms without lumps. Add milk to paste and stir constantly until thickened. Add cheese to satisfy your own taste and stir until melted. Remove from heat. Drain asparagus. In a casserole dish, layer half of the asparagus and nuts, 1 sliced egg and half the sauce. Repeat layering with remaining ingredients. Top with cracker crumbs and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly and crumbs are golden brown.

title: one-egg wonder cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl. Add 1/2 liquid and egg.
Beat 1 minute. Add remaining liquid and beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Unwrap the caramels and place in microwave-safe bowl.
Grease bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Combine soup, water, sour cream and parsley in bowl; mix well.
Alternate layers of potatoes, sprinkled with salt and pepper, and sauce in greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with pork chops.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: upbeat barbecue beans
directions: Drain beans.
Pour into baking container.
Mix brown sugar, mustard and barbecue sauce.
Sprinkle on seasoned salt to taste. Bake at 325° until bottom of beans is firm.

title: foxy steak kebabs
directions: In a shallow glass dish, combine soy sauce, honey, ginger, garlic, lemon peel and red hot pepper flakes.
Mix well.
Add beef.
Stir to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: supreme carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Mix sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time. Stir in carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Pour into a well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sister cuba's famous butter roll
directions: Mix shortening, flour and 1/2 cup of milk together.
Take dough mixture as you would biscuit dough and roll out; separate dough to make five saucer size pancakes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine sugar, oil and boiling water.
Add cold water. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to mixture plus egg.
Add flour.
Knead 3 to 5 minutes well.
Grease a bowl and place dough in it in the refrigerator until ready to use.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil potato until tender.
Peel off skin and mash.
Add confectioners' sugar until stiff dough is formed.
Roll our on a sugared board until thin.
Spread with peanut butter to cover the potato dough.
Roll up like a jellyroll.
Chill, then cut into thin slices.

title: maud's drop donuts
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, sour cream, milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Drop with donut maker. Brown in oil.
Drain on paper towels.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
In a large bowl, cream oleo and sugar with eggs.
In a separate bowl, sift together: flour, soda, and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add bananas, nuts, vanilla, and sour cream.
Mix well and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Use 1 large or 2 medium greased and floured bread pans.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Place chopped rhubarb in pie shell and mix sugar, eggs, flour, tapioca and cream.
Pour over rhubarb and dot well with butter.
Bake in 425° oven for 12 minutes and reduce heat to 350° and bake 1 hour.

title: calico bean hot dish(serves 8)
directions: Saute hamburger, bacon and onion until light brown.
Partially drain beans.
Thoroughly mix rest of ingredients; add to meat and beans.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: baked ziti and cheese
directions: Bake sausage for 30 minutes at 350°; cool.
Slice in thin pieces.
Saute mushrooms, green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Remove vegetables.
Blend flour into butter; stir in milk.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture begins to boil. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese, Parmesan or Romano cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth.
Set aside and keep warm.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Saute onions, celery, garlic and bell pepper in butter until wilted.
Add Worcestershire sauce, crab meat and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook about 15 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Then add bread which has been soaked in the milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Stuff crab shells with mixture.
Sprinkle tops of crabs with bread crumbs and bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: angel pie(needs 12 hours to set)
directions: Beat 3 egg whites and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar; gradually add 1 cup of sugar; beat stiff.
Line spring-form pan with paper and spread mixture flat.
Bake at 275° for 60 minutes.
Cool. Whip 1 cup whipping cream and sweeten.
Spread half of cream over cooled meringue.
Make custard.

title: skillet corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put butter in 9-inch iron skillet and heat in oven.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in 1 cup milk and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk.
Pour mixture into skillet.
Pour 1 cup milk over cornbread mixture.
Do not stir in!
Bake for 35 minutes.
This cornbread has a custard layer.
Serve hot from skillet with butter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped green peppers
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place a layer of sliced egg in the bottom of casserole.
Cover with a layer of green pepper, then cheese, repeating until all is used.
Add salt and pepper. Pour the milk over the mixture.
Cover with bread crumbs that have been mixed with the butter or margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Chop/shred cabbage and combine with red and green peppers. Mix salt, sugar, vinegar and water.
Pour this over cabbage and peppers.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
Then roll in chopped nuts or dried beef pieces.
Serve with crackers.

title: pizza brunch
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Separate rolls into triangles; form a crust in pan.
Seal edges together.
Combine eggs, milk and spices in bowl; beat until smooth.
Layer sausage, Cheddar cheese and mushrooms (drained) over crust.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until filling is set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bean salad
directions: Choose 3 of the beans and drain. Heat the sugar, vinegar, oil and salt until dissolved. Pour over veggies and refrigerate overnight.

title: hummus
directions: In a blender, combine 1/4 of the peas, lemon juice, water, oil, garlic and parsley.
Blend on high speed, adding the remaining peas and the tahini, until it is all pureed.
Salt to taste.
Serve with wedges of pita bread and carrot and celery sticks.
Makes 2 cups.

title: jalapeno broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain and place in greased casserole dish.
Saute onion in oleo.
Mix soup, Cheez Whiz, onion and sour cream.
Pour over broccoli and top with cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: kit kat bars
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with the crackers.
(Separate them into individual squares, this way the crackers lay better in the pan.)

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Combine the above ingredients in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: very very good mincemeat(this recipe was over 100 years old when i got it in 1968)
directions: Mix all but meat and spices.
Boil until raisins are tender.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: homemade baby wipes
directions: You will need an old baby wipe container.

title: chocolate-pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until done; brown on top.

title: soul gumbo recipe
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients in a Dutch oven or other large pot.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer while preparing remainder of recipe.

title: poor man's pecan pie(yields 2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs; cream in sugar and butter and add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, bring sugar, butter, milk and cocoa to a boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla; stir for a few minutes to cool slightly.
Add oats and pecans.
Drop mixture by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Let cool and harden.
Each cookie contains 115 calories, 34% from fat.
Yields 30 large cookies.

title: lemon dessert loaf
directions: Line a loaf pan with the vanilla wafers.
Mix Cool Whip, lemon juice and condensed milk together.
Pour into pan and freeze overnight.
Invert on plate to serve.

title: valley fresh turkey supreme
directions: Drain and cut Valley Fresh white turkey into bite-size pieces. Mix together mayonnaise, mustard, sage and white pepper.
Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cream the cheese until smooth.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk.

title: korean ribs
directions: Cut steak into strips about 1 or 1 1/2 inch long.
Marinate in remaining ingredients for about 30 minutes or more.
Place on broiler pan and broil on both sides until brown; 10 to 15 minutes on each side.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt stick of oleo or butter in casserole dish (in oven).
Mix sugar, flour and baking powder in bowl.
Put fruit into melted butter.
Sprinkle flour mixture over fruit.
Pour milk over flour mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: susan's hush puppies
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together and set aside for 5 to 10 minutes to sour; add egg and beat well.
In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, corn meal mix and onion, mixing well.
Add only enough of the milk mixture to moisten the dry ingredients; the batter should be thick (don't overmix).
Allow batter to stand at room temperature for at least 30 minutes.
Using a small spoon, drop batter into hot oil, rinsing the spoon in between the drops of batter in a glass of cold water.
Avoid stirring the batter.
Cook until medium brown and floating.
Makes 1 dozen hush puppies.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add egg yolks.
Add milk; beat. Cook on medium heat until thick.
When it begins to thicken, beat again.
Remove from heat when thick and creamy.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add meringue and brown. Makes 1 pie.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Put grits in boiling salt water to cook.
When grits are done, add oleo and cheese that have been cut into small portions.
Stir until both are completely melted.
Beat eggs; place in measuring cup, add milk to make one cup.
Stir into grits.
Pour grits mixture into casserole and bake in a 325° oven until top is brown. Serve as a vegetable casserole with dinner.
Can also be stored in refrigerator.
Slice and heat in the microwave for a quick breakfast treat.

title: chocolate whoopie pies
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, bananas and egg.
Add Crisco.
Sift flour and add salt.
Dissolve baking soda in sour milk and add to other mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased loaf pan.

title: flan
directions: Melt 1 cup sugar in a 9-inch cake pan until golden color. Coat bottom and sides with sugar caramel.
In blender, combine eggs, cream cheese, sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Blend. Pour mixture into caramelized pan.
Place pan into a pan of water and bake about 1 hour.
Cool and invert.

title: banana frosted
directions: Peel banana; slice into a bowl.
Beat with egg beater or electric mixer until smooth and creamy.
Mix well.
Serve immediately.

title: watermelon lemon slush
directions: In teapot, pour boiling water over Lemon Soother Herbal tea bags; cover and brew 5 minutes; remove tea bags.
Stir in sugar; chill.
In blender, process tea with watermelon until blended.
Add ice cubes, one at a time.
Process at high speed until blended. Garnish, if desired, with a wedge of watermelon.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: green tomato pickle
directions: Chop onions and peppers; mix all vegetables with 1/2 cup salt. Let stand
overnight.
Drain.
Tie
mixed
spices in bag and simmer 20 minutes.
Pack
in
hot
jars.
This recipe makes approximately 28 pints.

title: sunday roast
directions: Place roast on large sheet of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle dry soup mix, salt and pepper over roast.
Spread mushroom soup over all.
Seal foil and bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: shipwreck
directions: Saute the onions. Place in casserole dish. Spread a layer of potatoes over the onions. Add the hamburger over the potatoes. Season.
Add layers of the rice, tomatoes, celery and beans. Garnish with the green pepper or bacon.
Bake 2 hours.
Makes a nice large casserole.

title: one cup cobbler
directions: Place butter in casserole dish and place in oven to melt. Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour into dish over melted butter, then pour in one can of peaches or fruit of choice.
Do not mix.
Place in 350-400 degree oven until done.

title: pasta salad(given to clo fletcher by clara hollingsworth)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and cool. Slice cucumbers, dice cauliflower and broccoli.
Chop cheese.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Add pepperoni and mayonnaise (just enough to make it slippery).
Right before serving, add Caesar salad dressing (I use most of a small bottle, or as much as you like).

title: grandma's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except one bag of chips.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle the second bag of chips on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: easy popcorn balls
directions: Bring Jell-O, sugar and syrup to a boil.
Mix with popcorn. Butter hands and form into balls.
Place balls on wax paper to cool.

title: russian eggs
directions: Slice eggs in halves; remove yolks.
In medium bowl, mix egg yolks, mayo, ketchup, salt, pepper and mustard until smooth.
With teaspoon, place mixture in clean dry egg white halves.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pina colada muffins
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Add pineapple, coconut, pecans and both flavorings.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full because it doesn't rise very much.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in marshmallows until dissolved.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add cream cheese and whip until smooth.
Let set 15 minutes.
Add pineapple and mayonnaise.
Fold in whipped cream.
Add pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: potato pudding
directions: Peel potatoes.
Place in cold water until ready to grate.
Dry potatoes and grate.
Grate onion and add to potatoes.
Stir in well beaten eggs, hot milk, melted butter and salt.
Pour into well buttered 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle parsley over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until golden brown. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken with sweet onion sauce(kammama)
directions: Cut the chickens in pieces.
Put them in a thick-bottomed saucepan with the offal.
Add salt, saffron, pepper, the stick of cinnamon and one sliced onion and a glassful of water.
Boil for a few minutes over a moderate heat and mix the spices well.
Add the onions, cut in rings 1 cm (1/2-inch) thick, and the tomatoes, peeled, seeded and cut in half.
After a few minutes boiling, remove the chicken pieces and put them in an ovenproof dish. Immediately add the sugar and cinnamon to the sauce.
Mix well and put the onions and tomatoes on top of the chicken with the sauce poured over the top.
Cook in the oven, basting often.
When cooked, pour the sauce into a saucepan and boil it down until it becomes thick and syrupy.
When the chickens are cooked and the onions gold and caramelized on top, remove from the oven.
Arrange on a dish with the onions on top of the chicken pieces and pour the sauce over.
Serve at once.

title: turkey pie
directions: Mix together and put in crust.
Also put crust on top and seal.
Make gravy with 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Put on table and let each put his own gravy on pie.
Cook at 425° for 15 minutes; lower heat to 400° and cook 50 minutes in all.

title: fettuccine supreme
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions; drain.
In a large bowl, blend together next 4 ingredients.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Toss fettuccine with shrimp mixture.
Pour into a 3-quart prepared baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Cover, bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring to a boil and let cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix in the order given.
Mix well.
Separate into 4 sections. Roll into the shape of a cylinder.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate or freeze as needed.
The cylinders can be frozen for 6 months.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Arrange rhubarb in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar and Jell-O over rhubarb.
Pour water over all.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all.
Cut butter in thin slices and put over top of cake mix.
Do not mix, beat or stir.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.
Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: iced coffee
directions: Mix the ingredients together in a pitcher and leave in the refrigerator for 4 hours.

title: quick lasagne(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground meat into plastic colander over mixing bowl; microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring at 2 1/2 minutes. Discard drippings.
Combine meat, sauce, water and Italian seasoning; set aside.
Combine Ricotta cheese, egg, parsley, pepper and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese in a separate bowl.
Pour 1/4 inch of meat sauce in a baking dish.
Layer noodles, Ricotta cheese mixture and then Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Simmer (1/3 power) for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle on remaining Parmesan cheese.
Allow to stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: potato wedges
directions: Scrub unpeeled potatoes well.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise, then cut into even wedges.
Boil for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
Pat dry.
Spread wedges in a single layer on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with oil, spices and herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for another 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat butter and sugar creamy until blended.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Stir in vanilla and zucchini.
Add to dry ingredients alternately with milk, stirring until smooth. Include nuts in last addition.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack to cool.
Put on glaze.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cheese.
Pour into a greased 11-inch Corning Ware baking dish.
Chill overnight. After chilling, remove from refrigerator and top with the grated cheese.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with toast or English muffins.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Arrange meat in bottom of glass baking dish (do not brown). Place a layer of the vegetables over the meat; salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle the tapioca over this mixture.
Pour sauce and water over this.
Do not stir.
Seal with foil.
Place in a 325° oven for 2 hours or until ready to serve.
This may be frozen before cooking.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, salt, spices and beets 10 minutes.
Add hard-cooked eggs.
Chill several days.

title: beer batter for shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp, oil and coconut.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Heat oil to 350°.
Dip shrimp in batter, then roll in coconut.
Fry until golden brown.
Don't let coconut burn.
May leave off coconut if you wish.
Delicious either way.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Add corn muffin mix and cheese; mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in greased casserole dish until brown on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stewed shrimp
directions: Bone chicken breast.
Cut in slivers.
Saute in margarine; set aside.
Wash and cut vegetables; stir-fry in remaining fat until crisp.
Add salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Serve with rice or potatoes; cut recipe in half for small group or serve as a salad next day.

title: beef vegetable dinner(pressure saucepan cooking)
directions: Cut beef into cubes.
Brown in fat in cooker.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Cover pressure saucepan and set cooking control at 10 pounds pressure.
Cook for 5 minutes after the control jiggles.
Cool cooker for 5 minutes, then place saucepan under the faucet until pressure reaches zero.
Open pan and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, cherries, crushed pecans and cool whip. Spread in a glass 9 x 9 dish.
Top with pecan halves as a garnish. *Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Will be firm.

title: quick hot cross buns
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in raisins (or currants) and mixed fruit.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; beat until almost smooth. Add flour mixture; mix well.
Knead dough on slightly floured surface 10 times.
Shape dough into 12 balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 18 to 20 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool. When cooled, make glaze by combining confectioners sugar, 1/8 teaspoon vanilla and milk; mix well.
Make a cross on top of each bun with glaze.
Serves 12.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Flour chicken strips and saute in large skillet.
Remove chicken from pan and set aside.
Add brown sugar, corn starch, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Stir until thick.
Add chicken to sauce and simmer until all is hot.
I sometimes add small can of pineapple juice to make larger amount of sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: black beans and yellow rice
directions: Place cooked yellow rice on a serving platter.
Spread heated beans on top.
Then spread salsa, sour cream and chopped vegetables.
Serve with hot sauce and olive oil.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Then add all other ingredients.
Stir good.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla cookies with chocolate-coconut topping
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a food processor, or with an electric mixer, blend the flour, sugar, margarine, egg, vanilla and salt to form a stiff dough.

Roll 1/2 tablespoon of the dough into a ball; repeat with the remaining dough to make 32 cookies. Place the cookies 1 inch apart on a nonstick baking sheet; lightly press each one with your fingers to flatten slightly.
Bake until the cookies are firm and the bottoms are lightly golden, 10 to 15 minutes.
Transfer the cookies to a rack to cool.
Drizzle each cooled cookie with the chocolate and sprinkle evenly with the coconut.
Serves 16.

title: mexican dip
directions: This is a layered dip that is excellent!
It is served on a large platter or placed in a large, shallow dish and is eaten using corn chips, such as Doritos, Tostitos, tortilla strips, etc., to scoop it up.
It is assembled something like a pizza.

title: meatballs with mushroom gravy
directions: Mix ground chuck, onion, eggs, salt, pepper and crackers.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
(Slightly flatten for quicker cooking time.)
Brown in skillet with lid (electric skillet works best) until both sides are brown.
Fill skillet 1/2 with water and let simmer 30 minutes.
Add mushroom soup and sliced mushrooms. Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Melt butter in a square Pyrex dish.
Add apples.
Cover with cinnamon and the sugar.
(Use juice of 1 lemon with canned apples, if desired.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cherry delight pie
directions: Mix butter and crumbs, put in long pan and let chill.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole. Bake 45 minutes at 325°. Serve warm with cocktail rye bread.

title: fondue cheese appetizers
directions: Cut cheese into 3/4-inch cubes.
Combine egg and milk.
Dip cheese into egg mixture and coat with crumbs.
Repeat.
Fry in 1 1/2-inches of hot oil for 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain. Makes 1 dozen.
To make ahead, prepare as directed.
Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush toasted corn flakes and mix with butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water 5 minutes.
Drain well. Mix sour cream and soup together.
Fold in squash and onion. Melt stick of butter.
Add box of herb seasoned croutons.
Layer bottom of dish with croutons.
Add squash mixture and top with croutons.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rosy glow punch
directions: Combine juices; pour into punch bowl.
Add scoops of sherbet. Slowly add ginger ale.
Serves 50 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: ham baked in a blanket
directions: Cook ham in
open roasting pan, fat side up. Roll dough in sheet and
cover
ham well.
Place in hot oven preheated to 400° to bake dough.
Bake ham, covered, with dough at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
Dough
will
not
be
edible, but ham should be delicious.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil potatoes for 15 minutes; peel and cut in halves. Place in buttered baking dish. Combine sugar, salt, butter and water. Boil 3 minutes. Pour syrup over potatoes. Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Serves 6.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Step 1:
Mix pretzels, sugar and melted butter together; spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: parmesan rosemary pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into four rectangles on smooth side of large cutting board.
Press seams to seal.
Place cream cheese in small batter bowl.
Grate Parmesan cheese over batter bowl using Deluxe Cheese Grater.
Snip rosemary using kitchen shears; add to cheese mixture.
Mix well using small Mix N Scraper.
Using small spreader, spread each rectangle with 2 tbsp. cheese mixture to within 1/4 inch of edges.
Starting at short side roll up each rectangle; pinch edges to seal.
Cut each roll crosswise into six slices using serrated bread knife for a total of 24 slices.
Place slices, cut-side down, on a large round stone. Bake 12 - 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven to cooling rack.
Serve warm using serving spatula.

title: virginia ham biscuits
directions: Dice onion and saute in butter until translucent.
Add mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire.
Spread this mixture on split rolls, both top and bottom half.
Top with ham and cheese. Close rolls, wrap in foil and warm in oven.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Combine in a deep bowl the first 3 ingredients.
Crumb and mix together the next 4 ingredients.
Take out 1 cup of crumbs for the top of cake.
Mix both mixtures together, putting the 1 cup of crumbs over top of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue leg of lamb
directions: Combine together well all ingredients except lamb.
Add lamb. Coat, cover and marinate for at least 12 hours.
Place lamb on grill over medium heat.
Grill as you would a London broil, brushing with marinade.
Slice like a London broil.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add all other ingredients.
Congeal and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the small onion and celery with chicken.
Bone chicken. Cut in large pieces.
Crumble 1/2 box crackers and line the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with 1/2 stick margarine. Arrange chicken atop crumbs.
Add chestnuts to chicken.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Add on top of water chestnuts.
Put balance of cracker crumbs on top and dot with margarine.
Bake at 420° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken, soups, vegetables, milk, thyme, salt and pepper together in a bowl.
Place 1 pie crust at bottom of pie dish, then add mixture.
Place other pie crust on top.
Seal; bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue hotdogs
directions: Place grape jelly and chili sauce in a 2 qt. pan.
Stir over low heat until jelly is melted.
Pour into crockpot and add hotdogs or kielbasa.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hr.

title: sausage loaf
directions: Let frozen loaf bread thaw and rise according to directions on container.
Roll out when thawed.
Fry and drain sausage well.
In a bowl mix cooked sausage, cheese (to your taste) and eggs that are already beaten. Pour mixture onto bread rolls.
Fold bread over mixture, putting fold on bottom of pan.
Bake until bread is done at 350° to 400°.

title: vegetable vinaigrette salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and place in large bowl with cover. Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss and marinate overnight or several days.

title: white gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and mix until crumbly.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups of the crumbs.
Stir the spices into the sugar and flour mixture, then add the milk, soda and eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Spray a 9 x 14-inch pan with cooking spray, then sprinkle 1/2 of the reserved crumbs on the bottom of the pan. Pour in batter, then sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chocolate marshmallow torte
directions: Pour 1 cup milk and marshmallows together.
Melt.
Cool in refrigerator.
Crush Oreos in
bottom
of
9 x 12-inch pan. Melt butter and pour over Oreos.
Pat
in
bottom of pan.
Mix puddings and milk together as directed.
Pour over Oreo crust. Add Cool Whip to marshmallow mixture.
Pour over pudding.
Top with few Oreo crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: frozen chocolate dessert
directions: Cream together oleo, powdered sugar and chocolate.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat at high speed. Pour over crust and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cover with ice cream (let soften briefly, cut in slices with sharp knife).
Cover with remaining crumbs and freeze.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat egg with milk and add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pan.
Let stand 45 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until meat is done and onion is clear.
Add green beans, tomato soup and mushroom stems and pieces.
Salt and pepper mixture to taste and put in a casserole dish.
Mash potatoes and cover the top of the meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown on top.

title: medium white sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine over low heat.
Add flour and pepper. Stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk and return to heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all of the ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Pare large potatoes and cover with cold water.
Let stand for 12 hours.
Pour off water and grate potatoes.
Drain well.
Add eggs and mix lightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop from tablespoon onto hot well-greased skillet and brown on both sides.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, milk and vanilla instant pudding.
Put on cake.
Put 1 can of	pineapple
on top of cream cheese and pudding mixture. Spread medium Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine lemonade and sweetened condensed milk; stir well. Fold in whipped topping and grated lemon rind, if desired.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Keeps well. Decorate with thin lemon slices, if desired.

title: pancake syrup(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Stir together syrup, sugars, water and salt in a saucepan and slowly bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Let boil 5 minutes. Add maple flavor to taste.
Makes a little over a pint.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Heat the milk until scalded (do not boil).
Add the oil and sugar to the milk.
When the milk has cooled to lukewarm, add the yeast and two cups of flour.
Mix well until there are no lumps. Cover and let rise until doubled.
Then, add the remaining three cups of flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt.
Mix until the consistency of biscuit dough.
You can roll out the dough or refrigerate at this point.
Dough may be kept in the refrigerator five or more days.

title: overnight french toast
directions: You will need a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Place rhubarb pieces on the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry jello over rhubarb, then sugar over jello followed by the miniature marshmallows.
Make cake according to directions on the box and pour over all the ingredients.
This concoction is baked for about 55 to 60 minutes at 350° or until cake portion tests done.
Cut into squares and turn each piece upside-down on serving dish to show pretty part.
Serve plain or with ice cream or whipped cream.
The marshmallows seem to disappear with only their sweetness and flavor remaining.

title: corn dumplings
directions: Mix baking mix, cornmeal and milk until dough forms.
Stir in corn. Drop dumplings by heaping spoonfuls onto your favorite boiling soup or stew.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes. Cover and cook 10 minutes more.

title: dill weed dip
