directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking pan.
Melt chocolate and shortening in saucepan.
Mix all other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes or until brownies start to pull away from sides of pan. Do not overbake.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in large saucepan over low heat; remove from heat and let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt; add to the first mixture and mix well until flour disappears.
Chill.
(This can be mixed, left in refrigerator overnight and baked the next day.)
Form into 1-inch balls, roll in granulated sugar and place on a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for two or three minutes.
Finish cooling on wire rack.

title: crunchy double chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl; beat together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients, mixing until thoroughly combined.
Add 2 cups of corn flakes, chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Drop by tablespoons in remaining cereal, coating dough completely.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°, about 15 minutes.

title: cassie's "homemade" cookies
directions: Spread frosting on cookies.
Store in closed plastic container. Put remaining frosting in freezer for later use.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add vanilla and mix. Mix nuts and flour.
Add to mixture.
Roll into small balls. Place on greased sheet.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or less. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Later repeat until they look like snow balls.

title: cucumber slices
directions: Peel the cucumber and cut into quarters lengthwise and remove the seeds.
Chop fairly fine.
Cream the cream cheese and add the salt and chives.
Add the cucumber just before serving the sandwiches to avoid having the mixture become too watery.
Spread on ovals or rounds or white bread with crusts removed.
These are to be served open-faced.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Grease pie plate, 1 large or 2 small.
Beat all ingredients together with electric mixer, about 2 minutes.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter, and eggs together.
Add cup of coconut and stir well.
Pour in prepared crust and bake at 300° until firm, about 35-40 minutes.

title: savory potatoes
directions: Combine water, salt and butter in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole. Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 3 or 4 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Stir in milk and potato flakes. Blend in sour cream, onion salt and egg.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Re-cover.

title: fresh homemade peach ice cream
directions: Mix thoroughly in blender.
Pour into freezer container and fill
with
fresh
sweet
milk
to freezer container line. Follow directions for operating freezer by the freezer maker.

title: chocolate-coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites with vanilla and salt until stiff.
Beat in sugar until mixture becomes glossy and stiff.
Fold in coconut and chocolate until blended.
Drop on cookie sheets, lightly greased.
Bake 20 minutes or until firm. Store in airtight container.

title: grandma white's fruitcake
directions: Pour pineapple juice over candied fruit and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and add to mixture.
Add fruit, nuts and Karo syrup.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into 3 greased loaf pans that have been lined with wax paper.
Bake at 250°
for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cool on cake rack and remove wax paper.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll into nickle sized balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 minutes at 375°.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: grandma mildred's sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice.
Place in jar.
Cover with sugar and vinegar.
Shake and let sugar mixture melt.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sopapilla
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mealy.
Add water to form dough.
Put on floured board. Knead until smooth.
Rest dough 20 minutes.
Roll thin as possible; cut into 2 1/2 to 3-inch squares.
Should puff as browning in oil.
After frying, sprinkle with powdered sugar, cinnamon sugar or honey.

title: potato, corn and chile soup
directions: Cook potatoes, corn and chiles in broth until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and heat through.
Do not boil.
Serve with flour tortillas.

title: dried apricot fruitcake
directions: Soak dates, apricots, raisins and currants in boiling water for 1 hour.
Stir often.
Mix together brown sugar, butter and pecans; add baking soda, flour, eggs and Grand Marnier.
Mix well.
Divide batter into 2 well-buttered bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours; then test for dryness.
Bake 10 minutes longer, if necessary, and test again.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove cake to rack to cool.

title: tang tea
directions: Mix.
Use 1/2 cup to 1 mug hot water.
Can add 2 teaspoons Burgundy.

title: party punch
directions: Mix in a large punch bowl the sherbet and pineapple
juice. Add ginger ale to taste.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in glass pie pan at 325° until center is set.
Sprinkle a little of the bacon on top before baking.

title: doggie biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, dry milk, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Mix in egg.
Add enough water so that mixture forms a ball.
Pat out dough 1/2-inch thick with your fingers on a lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Cut out with a cookie cutter and remove scraps.
Pat out scraps and proceed as before.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool on cake rack.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: steven's peanut butter apple treat
directions: Peel, core and slice apple into eighths.
Spread peanut butter on one side of sliced apple and serve.
Eat 'em up and enjoy!

title: grape-nuts pudding(double boiler)
directions: Beat egg in pan; add milk, sugar, salt, Grape-Nuts and raisins.
Stir all together well.
Cover and cook without stirring for 1/2 hour.

title: hot german rice salad
directions: Cook rice, following usual directions.
Fry bacon; drain.
Mix 1/4 cup bacon drippings with sugar, vinegar, water, onion and pepper; heat thoroughly.
Mix with rice, pimento and egg.
Toss with bacon, also.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve warm.
Feeds 4 as side dish.

title: oven-fried whiting fillets
directions: Rinse fish with cold water; pat dry with paper towels.
Cut fillets in 6 equal-size serving portions.
Combine oil, salt and garlic in oblong glass baking dish.
Put fish in mixture.
Let marinate 10 minutes; turn; marinate additional 10 minutes.
Remove fish from marinade, roll in Parmesan cheese, then in bread crumbs. Place fish on a well-greased baking sheet.
Bake in a hot (500°) oven 12 to 15 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Enjoyed by Vito Vergari.
Yields 6 servings.

title: santa skiparroons
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and place on oil paper in a dish or square pan.
Put in refrigerator and chill until firm. Cut in squares.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add all ingredients together.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dot with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve cold.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: For frosting, beat margarine or butter until fluffy.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and enough milk or cream to make frosting of good spreading consistency.
Stir in the reserved toasted pecans.

title: french fry casserole
directions: Heat soup, cheese and onion.
Pour over vegetables and fries. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy blue cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cheeses; cream well.
Blend in the 1/3 cup coconut, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and chill at least six hours.
Before serving time, combine last 3 ingredients on piece of wax paper.
Form cheese mixture into a ball and roll in pecan and parsley mixture until completely covered.
Place on crystal platter and serve with crackers.

title: bacon wrap water chestnuts
directions: Cut pound of bacon in 1/2.
Wrap each chestnut with bacon and stick with toothpick.
Melt sugar and catsup together; pour over chestnuts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 375° until bacon is done, around 1/2 hour.

title: meatball appetizer
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, flour and milk together.
Make into small balls and brown well.
Drain off fat.
Mix grape jelly and chili sauce; add meatballs.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir often so meatballs become well glazed.

title: green bean salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and stir gently.
Let stand for about 5 hours before serving.
Drain off liquid and serve.

title: yummy pork and noodles
directions: Stir-fry pork in oil with onion and mushrooms until pork is white inside.
Add can of diced tomatoes and seasoning.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.
Serves 4, or, if you eat like we do, it serves 2.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Soften butter and cheese.
Cream together until smooth and add vanilla.
Add sugar gradually and beat until smooth.
Add nuts.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Generously butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut or break bread into cubes.
Spread bread in bottom of dish.
Cover bread with shredded cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt, onion, etc.
(add crumbled bacon).
Pour mixture over bread and cheese. Cover and chill at least 12 hours, not more than 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and let stand for 10 minutes.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cool for about 40 minutes and serve.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In Dutch oven combine all ingredients except spinach and pasta. Heat about five minutes.
Add spinach; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add pasta, reheat and serve.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add extract to milk and then add alternately with the sifted dry ingredients to the butter mixture. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan or loaf pan.
If you wish, the following filling may be used.

title: carolina corn pudding
directions: Bake in buttered dish.
Place in pan of hot water and bake in moderate oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat lemon Jell-O and pineapple with juice, to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool.

title: henry's favorite chicken or turkey pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut turkey or chicken and potatoes into 1-inch chunks.
In a 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, heat turkey, potatoes, onion, (sausage), frozen mixed vegetables, undiluted cream of chicken soup and milk to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes, gently stirring occasionally.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Add vanilla.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto foil-lined cookie sheets. Preheat oven to 350°.
Place in oven.
Turn off heat immediately. Do not open oven until completely cold.
Even leave overnight if possible.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain well.
Put broccoli into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk until smooth and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat Bisquick and margarine until crumbs and sprinkle over cheese. Bake until topping is light brown (20 minutes).

title: pollo en fricase(chicken fricassee)
directions: Rinse chicken pieces under cold running water and pat dry with paper towels.
Put garlic, peppercorns, oregano, salt and onion powder in a mortar.
Pound until crushed.
Rub seasoning thoroughly into chicken pieces.
Place chicken in a bowl.
Mix olive oil and vinegar and pour over chicken.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Heat vegetable oil in a large pot, casserole or Dutch oven.
Add chicken pieces and cook over medium heat, turning occasionally, until lightly brown.
Add sofrito, tomato sauce, achiote and sage.
Saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add green pepper, stuffed olives and water to cover chicken pieces (about 1 cup). Cover and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes.
During the last 20 minutes, add potato chunks.
Chicken is done when it's tender and sauce has thickened a bit.
Serve over rice or with bianda.

title: holiday pecans
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in a small bowl. In a large bowl, beat 1 egg white until foamy and add pecan halves. Toss until well coated. Add sugar mixture to coated pecans and stir well until pecans are coated. Spread pecans on greased cookie sheet and dot with 4 teaspoons butter. Stir every 5 to 10 minutes. Bake 1 hour at 275°.

title: broccoli and cheese cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May bake in muffin pans or as one. Bake at 350°.

title: "twelve hour" cabbage slaw
directions: Chop vegetables thin into large airtight container.
Then boil sugar, vinegar and seasoning.
Pour over vegetables.
Let set 12 hours in refrigerator.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, pepper and onions.
Boil together 30 minutes. Thicken with 8 tablespoons flour.
Stir constantly and cook 10 minutes.
Makes 10 pints.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add broccoli and cook until thawed.
Warm up soup and Cheez Whiz.
Then place all ingredients in crock-pot and heat for 30 minutes on low or bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except potato chips. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with potato chips. Bake about 1 hour. Makes 12 servings.

title: pasta fasule
directions: Skin pepperoni roll and slice.
Cut slices into 4ths.
Put olive oil in bottom of large pot to cover the bottom.
Add oregano, garlic and pepperoni.
Cover and cook to blend

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil for 5 minutes the sugar and water. Add the peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer vegetables (should be loose pack) still frozen in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add salt, chestnuts and onions.
Mix soup with sour cream.
Pour mixture over the vegetables and top with crackers which have been mixed with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: yummy salad
directions: Drain pineapple, then mix with pie filling.
Add sweetened condensed milk (not evaporated milk) and pecans.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Place in glass bowl and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: nut milk
directions: Blend all ingredients well and use instead of milk on cereals, hot or cold.

title: orange salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box.
Mix in all ingredients. Place in refrigerator and allow to congeal.

title: peach topping
directions: In small bowl mix peaches and lemon juice together.
In 2-quart saucepan, stir together corn syrup and margarine. Stirring occasionally, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 5 minutes.
Add peaches.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over pancakes, waffles, French toast, pound cake, baked ham or chicken.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: rigatoni
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in butter.
Add hamburg and brown.
Mix tomato sauce, tomato paste, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Add to meat mixture.
Cook 1/2 hour in pressure cooker or simmer on slow heat for 2 to 3 hours.

title: country style steak
directions: Make patties from ground beef and brown on both sides in large skillet.
Drain off grease, reduce heat to simmer.
In a bowl combine chicken and mushroom soup with milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over beef patties and cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: macaroon cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Mix at low speed until well combined; mixture will be crumbly.
Press evenly into bottom of prepared pan.

title: no cholesterol brownies
directions: Melt the margarine in a large bowl.
Add all other ingredients except walnuts.
Mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread out batter evenly in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch metal pay sprayed with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Serves 16.
Calories per square:
Fat 4 g and cholesterol 0.

title: rosamarina
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, salt, flour, and juice from pineapple and oranges in pan.
Cook until thick.
Cook and rinse macaroni.
Mix with sauce and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Add fruits and Cool Whip.

title: rich dessert
directions: Mix together and chill.
Spoon up and enjoy.

title: low-carb barbecue beef
directions: Remove excess fat from beef.
Cut into 4 pieces.
Place beef in a 4 to 5-quart slow cooker.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over beef.
Cover and cook on low heat for 7 to 8 hours or until beef is tender.
Remove beef from slow cooker.
Cut into thin slices or shred; stir back into sauce.
Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes more, or until beef is hot.
Makes about 12 sandwiches. Serve on low-carb buns or alone with sugar-free coleslaw.

title: super delite banana pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes and then allow this crust to cool.

title: father george's kielbasi kaper
directions: You will need a large pot and 2-inch baking pan.

title: carrot salad
directions: Wash, peel and grate carrots.
Mix all ingredients.

title: country pot roast with gravy
directions: In a Dutch oven or 4 to 5-quart pot with cover, brown the meat very well on all sides.
(If meat has no fat, use some margarine for browning.)
Add the chopped onion and cook until onion is soft and translucent, but not brown.
Add 1/4 cup water and 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Cover and simmer 3 to 4 hours, until meat is tender and cooked through.
(Add extra water as needed during cooking.)

title: vegetable rotini
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Add vegetables for last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
In saucepan, gradually stir soup into cream cheese; add the milk, cheese and pepper.
Heat (on low) until cream cheese is melted, stirring often.
Add macaroni and vegetables.
Heat through.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to directions on package. Spread rice on bottom of buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Top with broccoli, ham, mushrooms and cheese. Blend soup, mayonnaise, mustard and curry. Pour soup mixture over all. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta casserole
directions: Combine pasta, sauce, salt, water and hamburger (or any meat you want) in 13 x 9 inch dish, mixing well.
Cover with foil and cook at 400° for 35 minutes.
Take out of oven and stir.
Put shredded cheese on top and bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes until done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil the chicken in water with 1 tablespoon salt and the bay leaves.
Cool, debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Boil spaghetti until tender, rinse and drain.
Melt margarine in large casserole; saute onion in margarine.
Add soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cut cheese into pieces and add to the mixture.
Stir until cheese melts and add the chicken and spaghetti.
Cover and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375° (add salt and pepper to taste).

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour; add eggs (1 at a time) and beat well after each addition.
Stir in all remaining ingredients. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and continue baking an additional 45 minutes or until it tests done.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix berries, cornstarch and 1 cup of sugar in bowl.
Spread in 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine butter, milk, salt, vanilla and 1/2 cup of sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in flour and baking powder. Pour evenly over blackberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Saute onions until soft, not browned.
Add paprika, tarragon and red wine vinegar.
Stir well.
Add chicken which has been rolled in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Add broth and sherry.
Cover pan.
Cook over low heat about 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to platter and keep warm.
Add sour cream to sauce in pan; blend well.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour over the chicken and serve with egg noodles.

title: tossed salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into
blender
for
short time.
Keeps well. Or may dice onion and shake in quart jar.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt stick of butter and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs; press.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips over crumbs.
Then sprinkle chocolate chips. Then sprinkle coconut and walnuts over chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Pour condensed milk over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Wash peas, cover with water and let soak over night.
Drain, add seasonings, peas and cover with water.
Cook 45 to 60 minute. Add more water if necessary to keep peas juicy.
To serve:
mix cooked peas with cooked rice.

title: john hancock special
directions: Cut crusts from bread; butter one side and place buttered side down on square cake pan.
Mix ham, mustard and seasonings and spread it over the bread.
Cover with slices of cheese and top with remaining 4 slices of bread, buttered side up.
Mix beaten egg and milk together and pour this over top layer.
Chill, covered, for 1 hour (or leave in refrigerator overnight).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour; serve immediately.

title: blueberry oatmeal muffins
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Add sugar and rolled oats. Beat together in a large bowl egg, milk and melted margarine.
Add the dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: hershey almond pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars with small amount of water; add Cool Whip. Mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: date macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix remaining ingredients together and fold into egg whites.
Place in buttered pie pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Preheat oven 425°.
Mix all dry ingredients together in large bowl; set aside.
Dissolve yeast in very warm water, then add oil and buttermilk.
Pour this mixture into dry ingredient mixture. Mix well, turn out onto well-floured cutting board (or pastry sheet) and knead lightly until dough is well-floured; now pat out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut biscuits and put on baking sheet.
Bake until brown.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan; stir over heat until sugar dissolves.
Bring to boiling point; let boil, without stirring, for about 7 minutes.
Cool; add fruit juices.
When ready to serve, pour over ice; add ginger ale.
Garnish with mint sprigs.
Serves 25.

title: best chicken saladwich
directions: Heat nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Melt margarine.
Add chicken.
Sprinkle chicken with 1/2 of garlic, taco seasoning, salt, pepper and 2 dashes of Worcestershire per breast half.
Turn and repeat other side.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Turn and cook until done.
Serve on warmed onion rolls; top with your favorite condiments.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together well. Place in a large, greased baking pan and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer and chill overnight or at least 8 hours.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown beef with onions. Add taco seasoning mix and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Layer meat mixture with shells, sour cream and cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat together sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in pastry shell.
Add almond extract to cherry filling and chill overnight.

title: onion mushroom soup
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook about 8 minutes until tender.
Add mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes. Add broth, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Before serving, sprinkle with Parmesan.
Yields 6 cups.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Pour all the ingredients into a bowl and mix until fluffy. Grease Bundt pan.
Preheat oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
Bake for 40 minutes.
This is wonderful served for breakfast or dinner.

title: hanley's barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to boil, then simmer to desired thickness.
Cook meat slowly and baste frequently.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook Tater Tots as directions call for. Mash up Tater Tots; line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put in drained ground beef.
Mix mushroom soup with water; pour over top of ground beef.
Sprinkle cheeses over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until cheese is golden brown.
Serves about 6.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa. Add remaining ingredients. Mix and pour into deep-dish unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: oven baked stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours or until tender.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Add the chocolate to milk and heat in a double boiler.
When chocolate is melted, beat with a rotary eggbeater until well blended.
Combine sugar (1 cup), flour and salt.
Add gradually to the chocolate mixture and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Then continue cooking for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: whiskey sauce
directions: Cook butter and sugar in a double boiler until mixture is thick and sugar is dissolved.
Add spoonful of mixture to egg, then stir egg into butter-sugar mixture.
Cool slightly; add whiskey.
Serve hot or cold over Bread Pudding.

title: pineapple or strawberry delight
directions: Beat cream cheese and eggs until smooth.
Add sugar and mix. Stir in
Cool Whip; add pineapple or strawberries.
Line bowl with vanilla wafers.
Alternate mixture until all is used up.
Set in refrigerator.
Set overnight.

title: easy chicken with potatoes
directions: Put chicken pieces in lightly greased Pyrex pan, 9 x 13-inch. Add potatoes, cut up in large pieces, chopped onions and spices plus salt and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Mix apples, cranberries and granulated sugar and put in a 10 X 13 inch pan. Mix
oatmeal, brown sugar, flour, pecans and butter well and put on top of apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jello balls
directions: Mix ingredients, then put mixture in refrigerator to chill. (If you want different colors, half the mixture before adding the jello.)
Roll into little balls.
Leave a little jello in a saucer to roll balls in.
When they set awhile, they firm up.

title: frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick, like a ball.
Mix Crisco and sugar.
Add your thickened flour and milk.
Mix well.
You may mix any type flavoring.
Top cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly,
add
other ingredients.
Mix well, by hand and pour into unbaked	pie
shell.
Bake 45 minutes or until done at 300°.
Makes 9-inch pie.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain and cool.
Cut onion and pepper in round slices and mix with cooked carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate 12 hours or more.
Drain and serve.
This mixture should keep for 2 weeks.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix, 2 eggs and 1 stick margarine.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain fat.
Mix cream cheese with beef.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle with grated cheese. Add biscuits to the top and bake until brown at 400°.

title: chimichangas
directions: Combine chicken, salsa, onions, chili powder and salt in a saucepan; simmer until most of the liquid is evaporated.

title: apricot bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove apricots and set aside.
Cool liquid and add eggs, soda, flour and pecans, mixing well.
Add reserved apricots. Place in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: overnight macaroons
directions: The night before, mix together oatmeal, brown sugar and oil. Next morning, mix in beaten eggs, salt and almond flavoring.
Drop from teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: rita's fruit salad
directions: Drain the fruit cocktail.
Sprinkle the jello over the fruit; stir and let set for 30 minutes.
Stir in the sour cream and Cool Whip.
Next, add the remaining ingredients in desired quantities. Refrigerate before serving.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: country-style cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 9 inch ovenproof skillet or 9 inch square pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 6-8 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Stir together.
Pour into well-greased 9 X 13 pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: baked mixed vegetables
directions: Thaw out mixed vegetables.
Put in boiling water 1 to 2 minutes; drain.
Mix butter in vegetables.
Mix sour cream and Cheddar cheese together.
Layer it on top of vegetables.
Crumble Ritz crackers on the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mothers barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and boil 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a full rolling boil and boil for 3 1/2 minutes the white sugar, brown sugar, milk and Karo syrup.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, Marshmallow Fluff and vanilla.
Spray pan with Pam.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken breasts and reserve broth.
Saute celery, mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
Cook spaghetti in broth; drain.
Mix chicken, vegetables, soup, sour cream and spaghetti.
Layer spaghetti and cheese, ending with cheese and crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° until bubbly throughout.

title: tuna pie
directions: In large pan, cook onion and potato in water, covered until tender.
Drain off liquid.
Stir in soup, milk, cheese, lemon juice, dill and pepper.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in vegetables and tuna.
Spoon into ungreased 2-quart casserole.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar and melted shortening in bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Fold in flour and pecans; do not beat.
Spoon into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool.
Wrap in plastic wrap or foil overnight before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, celery, rice, soup, margarine and Cheez Whiz in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: fiesta corn salad
directions: Mix and chill for 3 hours (covered).

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into thin rings.
Do not pare.
Slice onions into thin rings.
Cut peppers in fine strips.
Dissolve salt in ice water and pour over sliced vegetables.
Let stand 3 hours and then drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar, and spices and bring to a boil.
Add drained vegetables and heat just to boiling point.
Do not boil.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Add flour, baking soda and salt together; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by well-rounded spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple-coconut custard pie
directions: Blend all together and pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake until brown or about 45 minutes at 325°.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil until well blended.
Add dry ingredients, a little at a time until well blended.
Add fruit, nuts and coconut and beat again.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: pork chops (crock-pot)
directions: Combine flour and seasonings in shallow pan.
Coat chops in mixture and brown in frying pan with oil.
Place browned chops in crock-pot.
Cover with chicken soup.
Rinse can with 1/4 can of water, adding to soup.
Cook on low heat for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften and drain pineapple.
Combine all ingredients.
Place mixture in refrigerator to become firm.
Once firm shape into a ball.
Chop 1 1/2 cups pecans.
Roll ball until covered with pecans.

title: olive spread
directions: Remove pimientos from olives.
Stir all ingredients together. Mixture will be mushy but thickens as it stands.
Refrigerate for 24 to 48 hours.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar.
Mix finely cut dates with flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla.
Mix all together and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Do not overbake.
Leave in pan until nearly cold and cut into bars.

title: coconut butter balls
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy, gradually adding sugar, then vanilla.
Blend in flour, then coconut.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Refrigerate about 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread the filling evenly on the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer the undrained pineapple on top of cherries.
Sprinkle the cake mix over pineapple.
Cover with melted butter.
Top with coconut and nutmeats.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: polish crullers(chrusciki)
directions: Add salt to eggs and beat until thick.
Add sugar and flavoring (grated lemon rind could be used instead of brandy). Beat good; add sour cream and flour, mixing well.
Knead on floured board until dough blisters.
Cut into 3 parts and roll each separately.
Roll dough out thin.
Cut into slanted strips, 4-inches long, 1 1/2-inches wide.
Slit each piece in center; pull one end through slit.
Fry in hot grease until lightly browned. Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: play dough
directions: Thoroughly mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and food coloring of your choice until color desired.
Cook three minutes or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Turn out and knead immediately.
Store in airtight container and keep refrigerated. May also be kept in plastic container in classroom for weeks.

title: herb boiled chicken
directions: Mix broth, lemon juice, basil, thyme and pepper and set aside. Place chicken on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 6 inches from heat 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, turning and brushing often with broth mixture.
Serves 4.

title: egg casserole
directions: Pat rolls together and put in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Put sausage on top of rolls.
Put cheese on top of sausage.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings and pour over cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 425° until the center is firm.
Cool.
Cut in squares. Wrap in foil and freeze or serve.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Combine everything in casserole baking dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Heat butter in large skillet.
Add onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Saute the ingredients.
Add tomato sauce, spaghetti mix, Cajun seasoning, Worcestershire, hot sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp; cover tightly and cook on low heat about one hour.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: salmon cabbage rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Add salmon and rice; mix well.
Immerse cabbage in boiling water until limp, 2 to 3 minutes; drain.
Slit heavy center vein of cabbage 2 inches up leaf.
Place 1/3 cup salmon mixture on each leaf; fold in sides and tuck ends under.
Place in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish, seam side down.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with cheese sauce; garnish with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: pam's mac-n-cheese
directions: Cook macaroni per package directions.
Stir together eggs, evaporated milk, salt and pepper; set aside.
Grate Cheddar cheese.
Cut up Velveeta in small blocks or slices.
In large dish or several small casserole dishes (loaf pans), layer macaroni and cheese
2 or 3 times.
Pour milk-egg mixture over Mac-N-Cheese. If more than 1 casserole dish is used, pour equal amount of milk-egg mixture over each dish of Mac-N-Cheese.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well. Add eggs and pecans.
Pour into two 8-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: In bowl, combine pretzels, sugar and margarine; set aside 1/2 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients and pour mixture over Doritos that have been emptied into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine soup and vegetables in casserole dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over soup and vegetables.
Place crescent rolls to cover.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes until brown or almost burnt.

title: wedding punch for fountain
directions: Makes 30 to 33 cups.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix jelly and mustard to desired taste.
Pour over wieners in crock-pot and simmer on low.
Serve hot.

title: chopped ham on buns
directions: Take 1 pound chopped ham.
Cut thin like dried beef.
Break in small pieces and put into sauce.
Then bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Serve on warm buns.
May be made in advance.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and butter until creamy, about 5 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Sift together plain flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, a little at a time, alternating with milk, begin with flour and end with flour.
Beat about 1 minute.
Add orange flavoring.
Beat afterward.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Pour mixture in and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Start in a cold oven.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute in oil in Dutch oven the chopped onions and shredded carrots.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add water and chicken bouillon cubes. Cook 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pesto-chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl; place ingredients in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve casserole immediately.

title: dirt cake
directions: Make 1 layer of ground Oreo cookies on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Put that aside.

title: dip dogs
directions: Put sticks in wieners.
Combine ingredients and dip wieners into mix.
French fry.

title: chris' lemon souffle
directions: Mix first three ingredients with egg yolks.
Add juice and grated rind of lemon to this mixture.
Fold stiffly beaten egg whites into mixture.
Place into spring pan and bake at 350° approximately 3/4 hour, until top has raised and is golden brown.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Cream eggs, oil and sugar; add soda, salt and flour together. Add remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces and steam 15 or 20 minutes until
just tender.
Put in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Place cheese slices on top to cover completely.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over top.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Add just enough milk to bring to proper consistency, and beat until fluffy. Add dill seed, chives and spinach.
Place in greased casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: ham-tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put 1/4 cup filling on each tortilla, spreading mixture to the edges.
Place 3 ham slices on top of cheese.
Roll up jelly roll style and place in plastic wrap; chill at least 3 hours.
Slice each roll into 8 pieces.
Serve with wooden picks.

title: southwestern chicken salad wraps
directions: Drain roasted peppers well, pressing between layers of paper towels; chop.
Stir together roasted peppers, chicken, and next 7 ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Stir pine nuts, if desired, in chicken mixture.
Spoon evenly over tortillas, and roll up.
These can be eaten as sandwiches, or each roll can be cut into 5 slices and served as appetizers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil
sugar,
milk
and butter or oleo together 10 minutes,
a boil
that can't be stirred down.
Remove from stove and
mix
in Marshmallow
Creme and peanut butter.
Mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered dish or pan.
Let cool; slice and eat.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add rice and raisins.
Sprinkle cinnamon and/or nutmeg on top.
Place pan inside a pan that has water in it.
I use the broiler pan for the water bath.
This makes the custard bake better.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until you can insert a knife and have it come out clean.

title: pastel cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking powder.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar and gelatin, beating well.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture, mixing well.
Force dough through cookie press or form in 1-inch balls, then flatten to 1/2 inch with bottom of floured glass.
Place on ungreased baking sheets and bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Makes about 10 dozen 1 to 1 1/2 inch cookies.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together seasoning, cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread on platter.
Place diced onions and diced green peppers over the spread.
Top with lettuce, then cheese and finally tomatoes.
Use as dip with chips of your choice.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Mix flour and cheese.
Cut unpeeled potatoes into bite size pieces.
Melt butter on cookie sheet. Shake potatoes in flour mixture using plastic bag or bowl with lid.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Stir once.

title: chocolate chess cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and eggs.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and eggs.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Pour over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: german's sweet chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottoms of 3 (9-inch) layer pans with waxed paper.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix and knead dough until smooth and shiny.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise double.
Divide in 2 parts.
Knead again and place in two greased baking pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
When loaves make hollow sound when tapped, take them out.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix next 6 ingredients together; pour batter over nuts.
Bake 1 hour; cool and invert on plate.
Prick top.
Mix next 3 ingredients in saucepan; melt and stir constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in rum.
Pour over cake; drizzle and smooth glaze evenly over top and sides, allowing cake to absorb glaze.

title: fruit cobbler(microwave)
directions: Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole with Pam.
Put in order: pie filling plus seasoning and Jiffy mix.
Sprinkle over pie filling. Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons melted margarine over all.
Microwave 15 to 20 minutes on High.

title: one day ahead cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip. Add coconut and nuts.
Spread one layer of vanilla wafers on bottom of glass baking dish; cover with mixture.
Then alternate layers of wafers and mixture.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cinnamon-laced sour cream pound cake
directions: Combine pecans, 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon, stirring well.
Set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well at medium speed of mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Cut carrots into thin slices and slice red onion.
Trim green pepper and cut into 1-inch chunks.
Drain marinated artichoke hearts and cut into quarters.
Drain marinated mushrooms.
Cut roasted red peppers into 1-inch wide strips.

title: candy coated popcorn
directions: Mix
the
first 2 ingredients.
Place in heavy saucepan over medium
heat
the
last
3 ingredients and bring to boil. Boil for 5
minutes.
Remove
from
heat and add 1/2 teaspoon soda and
1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and mix well. Put in oven and bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir 2 or 3 times during baking
to
coat thoroughly.
This
is
real
good
for those grandchildren.

title: crabmeat bites
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on English muffins.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cut each one into 6 pieces.
Serve immediately, or place in Ziploc bags and freeze.

title: party chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Roll and wrap each rolled breast with one strip of cooked bacon (do not allow bacon to get crisp). Secure with toothpick.
Pepper to taste.
Place in greased casserole that has been lined with slices of dried beef.
Mix sour cream and soup; pour over chicken.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Serve with apples or any fruit.

title: chicken with ham
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Remove skin.
Saute chicken in heated butter and oil on both sides until brown.
Alternately arrange chicken and folded ham slices in buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with crumbled basil leaves.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, until chicken is tender and juices run when pierced with fork.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: good chocolate candy
directions: Mix Carnation milk, sugar and salt.
Put in pan over low heat and heat to boiling point.
Boil 5 minutes exactly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add diced marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Stir until smooth and melted; spread on buttered platter.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased baking pan.
Put ketchup and 2 slices of bacon on top and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
You can use this for stuffed bell peppers.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Spread on both sides of buns. Put ham and cheese on buns.
Wrap with foil and heat in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: cheesy breakfast roll-ups(breakfast)
directions: In a saucepan cook mushrooms, onions, and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Drain.
Dividing mushroom mixture evenly, spoon along center of each tortilla.
Divide the 1 1/2 cups cheese among the tortillas.
Roll up tortillas and place seam side down in a greased 12x7x2 inch baking dish.
In a bowl stir together eggs, milk, flour, garlic and pepper sauce.
Pour over rolled up tortillas.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Put yeast in warm water to dissolve. Add salt, sugar and shortening to the scalded milk and let cool. Add mashed potatoes, eggs,
yeast, and flour. Let rise in warm place until doubled. Punch down and cut out donuts on a floured board. Let rise and fry in deep fat.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and margarine to a full rolling boil for 2 minutes in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Add oats and mix well. Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Let beans set in water overnight.
In the morning, drain all but 1 cup of water.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on high for 8 hours.

title: french onion soup
directions: Fry onions slowly in butter until dark brown.
Add water and bouillon.
Salt and pepper to taste and add sugar.
Thicken with flour.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: chocolate spectacular
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour and melted butter.
Press flour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until brown; let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and one container of Cool Whip in a large bowl; spread over crust.

title: mock liver pate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve in a mound with crackers.

title: grandmother's snickerdoodles
directions: Mix the shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add the flour, cream of tartar, salt and baking soda. Chill the dough at least 1 hour.
Roll dough into approximately 1-inch balls and roll the balls in a mixture of the 2 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and cloves. Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: pineapple tidbits
directions: Pat pineapple chunks dry on paper towel.
Wrap 1/2 piece bacon around chunk and secure with toothpick.
Place chunks in pan and broil in oven on 450° to 475° until bacon has browned.

title: broccoli and water chestnuts
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add broccoli to soup mixture.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sunday delight
directions: Place ice cream sandwiches in the bottom of a 13 x 8-inch pan. Drizzle with fudge topping and caramel topping.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans and cherries.
Keep cold until serving.

title: peanut butter power snack
directions: Mix all ingredients into bowl until well blended.
Place on crackers, bread or muffins.
If placed on bread or crackers, it could be microwaved.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Put aside until last.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar and spices in small bowl.
In large bowl, mix onion, celery and pepper.
Add liquid mixture.
Stir in olives, sliced meat and cheese.
Add pasta; toss until well coated. Chill.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: Saute the onion and bacon in the olive oil in a large saucepan, adding the garlic after 3 minutes.
Add the beans and pepper flakes; cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring carefully (so as not to break the beans).
Add the stock and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Finally, add the pasta and cook, uncovered, until al dente, about 15 minutes more.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Place broccoli in a baking dish.
In a separate bowl, mix soup, cheese, milk, mayonnaise and egg.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: crunchy coated chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Rinse the chicken under cold water; pat dry with a paper towel.
Melt the butter or margarine in a shallow roasting pan or casserole dish in the oven.
This will only take a minute or so.

title: easy chocolate frosting
directions: Melt together butter and chocolate.
Add milk, egg, sugar, vanilla.
Cook over slow heat to boiling, about 5 minutes.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Combine apple cider, water, sugar and ginger in a microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High until sugar dissolves and liquid begins to bubble, 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in rum and vanilla extract. Swirl in the butter.
Serve hot with a cinnamon stick in each cup.

title: meatloaf
directions: Mix together all the ingredients with your hands.
Put the meat loaf into a pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° until the loaf shrinks from the sides of the pan.
Pour off any grease and serve.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugars and eggs.
Blend well.
Add vanilla, syrup, peanut butter and baking soda.
Mix well. Gradually mix in oatmeal.
Add M&M's and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Dough can be refrigerated.
Makes 20 dozen cookies, approximately.

title: chunky vegetarian chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute green pepper, onion and garlic in oil until tender. Stir in all remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is cooked, stirring occasionally. If thinner chili is desired, add additional water. Makes 11 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost spinach; drain.
Place spinach in a bowl.
Add vegetable soup mix (dry).
Mix in the sour cream.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, tear the middle part of the Hawaiian bread into bite size pieces.
Put the dip in the middle of carved out bread.
Serve on a big plate, so you can arrange torn bread around dip.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken breast cubes, cole slaw mix and chopped onion in a large bowl.
Toast sesame seed and slivered almonds together for 7 to 8 minutes in a 350° oven until lightly browned.
Add to bowl. Crumple package of Ramen noodles and add to mixture.

title: cornbread ring
directions: Mix corn muffin mix and biscuit baking mix in large mixing bowl.
Blend in milk and egg.
Spray inside of 9 x 2-inch round glass dish and outside of 6-ounce glass cup with spray-on vegetable coating.
Cook in oven on full power for 3 to 4 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Layer 1:
One large avocado, chopped and sprinkled with lemon juice.
Substitution: One 16-ounce can guacamole.

title: mama hall's hot chocolate
directions: Using a small saucepan, bring these ingredients to a boil. Add enough milk to completely cover the bottom of the pan.
Heat until starting to boil.
Remove from heat.
Allow to cool slightly before drinking.

title: fork cookies
directions: Mix well.
Chill for 1 or 2 hours.
Pinch off dough and shape into balls.
Press flat with fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 or 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix limeade concentrate, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill several hours.

title: light and zesty chicken
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour Italian dressing over it.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Mix in rice, vegetables and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Then pour in chicken broth.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: cream cheese coconut frosting
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine.
Combine in mixing bowl; beat until smooth.
Continue beating and add sugar; mix well.
Add vanilla and coconut or pecans; mix well.
Spread between layers and over top and sides of cake.

title: garlic-herb mashed potatoes
directions: Take mature green beans and snap the ends. Lay them on a sheet
and dry for several days.

title: french toast
directions: Blend the first six ingredients.
Heat butter in skillet. Quickly dip bread slices in egg mixture, one at a time, just to moisten.
Fry in skillet until golden brown.
Top with powdered sugar and serve with syrup.

title: lemon buttered chicken
directions: Cut up small fryers.
Salt and pepper to taste after washing and patting dry.
Pour juice of lemons over chicken.
Let stand at room temperature at least 30 minutes.
Reserve liquid.
Melt butter in skillet.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Brown pieces of chicken on both sides.
Drain excess butter from skillet.
Replace chicken. Cover; simmer at low heat with reserved lemon juice until tender. Garnish with canned, drained figs and bananas sauteed in butter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Mix broccoli and onions with soup and cheese.
Add rice, salt and pepper to taste.
Dice butter and stick around mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs slowly and add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla, salt and half and half.
Slowly add milk.
Mix.
Pour into can and add enough milk to fill can 2/3 full.
Do not over fill, ice cream will fluff up.
Freeze and eat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.	Mix in all ingredients.
Cover. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: quick applesauce cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together in large bowl; set aside. Add applesauce to butter in large bowl, mixing well.
Stir in dry ingredients, raisins and nuts, blending well.
Line bottom of tube pan with waxed paper.
Pour batter into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 75 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix Karo, sugar and eggs.
Add pecans.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until middle does not shake.

title: mist yogurt pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixer bowl; blend at low speed and beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes until top of cake springs back when lightly touched in center.
Cool cake upright in pan for 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine all other ingredients, except broccoli and French onions.
Mix well, then add broccoli.
Mix broccoli in.
Put in a casserole dish.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, until firm.

title: ropa vieja
directions: Boil steak with 1 onion, 3 cloves garlic, 1 green pepper, 3 bay leaves, 1/4 cup vinegar and salt until tender.
Cool; then fry out remaining onions, peppers and garlic in olive oil.
Add meat, bay leaves, vinegar and small amount of broth.
Simmer until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in tomatoes and paste.
Heat.
Serve with black beans over white rice.

title: horatio's burnt creme
directions: Heat cream over low heat until bubbles form around edge of pan. Beat egg yolks and sugar together until thick, about 3 minutes. Gradually beat cream into egg yolks.
Stir in vanilla and pour into 6 (6-ounce) custard cups.
Place cups in pan of boiling water, 1/2-inch deep.
Bake in preheated oven (350° or a little less) until set, about 45 minutes.
(If custard cups are glass, bake at 325° for about an hour.)
Remove cups from water and refrigerate until chilled and sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Place on rack under broiler and cook until topping is medium brown.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken 'n noodle casserole
directions: To 2 quarts boiling water, add salt. Add noodles gradually. Cook, uncovered, at rapid boil 4 to 6 minutes or until tender when cut with a fork.
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain again. Mix noodles with chicken, soup, milk and cheese; pour into buttered casserole. Top with crushed potato chips. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 delicious servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crescent rolls.
Layer cooked meat (sausage, bacon, etc.).
Mix eggs and 1/2 to 1 cup milk; pour over meat.
Sprinkle top with cheese, oregano, salt and pepper.

title: strawberry-pecan cake
directions: Mix first 2 dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 3 layers.

title: southwestern rice and bean salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add well beaten egg and milk and mix well.
Mash ripe bananas and add to mixture.
Sift in dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Test with toothpick inserted near middle.
Toothpick will come out clean when done.
Serve hot or cold with or without butter or margarine.

title: honeyed chicken
directions: Rub the chicken pieces with lemon.
Sprinkle with half of the ginger and salt.
Combine oil, honey and the remaining ginger. Brush chicken with honey mixture.
Roast in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, basting occasionally with honey mixture.

title: low-fat chocolate chippers
directions: In large bowl, cream together shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients. Stir into creamed mixture, blending well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
With a non-fat cooking spray, grease cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoons (2 inches apart) on cookie sheet and bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken a la jacqueline
directions: Clean and cut in half chicken.
Rub with lemon.
Mix catsup and wine.
Pour half on chicken.
Season with all ingredients. Cut onion, pepper, mushrooms and carrots; put on top.
Turn chicken over after baking 1 hour.
Use the rest of the seasoning and bake for 1/2 hour more.
Bake at 375°.

title: turkey soup
directions: Melt butter in a large 8-quart stockpot.
Add onion, garlic, and celery; saute over medium-high heat 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth and next 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, and simmer at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Put chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sour cream & chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix crackers, poppy seed & margarine - spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30-45 minutes.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares(quick and easy)
directions: Combine caramels with 1/3 c. evaporated milk. Microwave until melted.
Set aside.
Grease at 9x13 pan.
Combine dry cake mix, butter, 1/3 c. evaporated milk and nuts.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in bottom of pan, patting with hands.
Bake at 350° for six minutes.
Put chocolate chips over baked mix, spread caramel mixture over chips.
Crumble remainder of dough over all. Bake 15-18 minutes at 350°. Cut into bars.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Combine all remaining ingredients and put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread cracker crumbs and butter over casserole.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in order given in large roaster or Dutch oven with tight fitting lid.
Bake at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.
No browning is necessary.
When done, the gravy is thick and brown. Stew may also be cooked on top burner over low heat in a very heavy roaster.
Stir occasionally.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Soften margarine and mix with sugar and peanut butter.
Roll in tiny balls and put in refrigerator to chill thoroughly.
Melt 1 12 oz pack chocolate morsels with 1/2 stick of paraffin.
Put peanut balls on toothpicks and dip in chocolate mixture.

title: chicken and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and cook chicken over medium-high heat.
Combine onion soup mix with cornstarch, ginger, water, soy sauce and vinegar.
Pour this mixture into skillet.
Add vegetables. Bring to a boil, then simmer 5 to 10 minutes, uncovered, until sauce is thickened.
Serve over hot rice.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream oleo and 2 sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add oats and chocolate bits. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; drain. Mix other ingredients and crumble crackers on top. Melt butter and pour over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together well. Pour into hot greased skillet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, wine vinegar and sugar and let refrigerate for 1 hour before mixing with rest of ingredients.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and water to make a gallon. Freeze and let thaw to slush.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat Crisco and peanut butter.
Add the 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat until combined.
Beat in egg, milk and vanilla. Beat in the flour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in the 1/4 cup sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately add kiss to the center.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender, then remove meat from bones and cut into small pieces and place in pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches).

title: burger noodle bake
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain off excess fat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add soup, cheese, sugar, sauce and salt. Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: crock-pot cheese potatoes
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
(They may be mixed the night before.)
Put into crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then on low for 3 hours (or start on low and cook longer).
If not thickened, remove lid and cook awhile on high, stirring occasionally.

title: fried crawdad
directions: In a bowl, combine the eggs, milk and Worcestershire sauce. In a separate bowl, combine the fish fry, flour, baking powder, salt, cayenne pepper and garlic powder.
Dip the crawfish in the egg mixture and coat with the dry mixture.
Heat the oil and deep fry
the breaded crawfish until golden.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: decadent chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Knock out excess.
Pour boiling water over chocolate and butter; let stand until melted.
Stir in vanilla and sugar; then whisk in egg yolks, one at a time, blending well after each.
Mix baking soda and sour cream into chocolate mixture.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to batter, mixing thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Stir in a quarter of the egg whites.
Scoop remaining whites on top of batter gently and fold in.
Pour the batter into prepared pan.
Set on middle rack of oven.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until edges pull away from side of pan and cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Unmold and cool completely before frosting.
Makes 12 portions.

title: freezing fresh strawberries and red raspberries
directions: Scald jello and add sugar; let cool and pour over berries in freezer boxes.
Fill boxes with syrup 1-inch below top of berries to allow for freezing.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Heat
oven
With
electric
mixer
on medium speed, blend together cream cheese, butter and sugar.
On low speed, blend
in eggs (one at a time).
Combine cake flour and baking powder.
Add to cheese mixture and blend until smooth. Pour into buttered and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: stuffed whole cabbage
directions: Remove core from cabbage and hollow out center.
Combine all other ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into cabbage shell. Place in 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish.
Microwave, tightly covered, on High for 17 minutes, turning after 9 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: whiskey punch
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Can be frozen and served as a slush or used immediately after mixed.

title: pear preserves
directions: Prepare pears by peeling, coring and slicing.
Place in a pot and add sugar.
Let sit overnight.
Cook on medium heat until they begin to boil, then put on low heat. Add lemon wedges, 1 to 3 lemons depending on what you prefer. Add pinch of salt.
Cook slowly, stirring often, to prevent from scorching.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: watergate
directions: Mix pudding and crushed pineapple (with juice) together.
Let sit until dissolved.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until eaten.
You can add chopped cherries for festive color.

title: amaretto cheese cake(heart healthy)
directions: Note:
Cottage and Ricotta cheeses must be drained in a coffee filter lined china cup overnight before proceeding with recipe (drain first, then weigh).

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put grated cheese on top.

title: brownie cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 30 (2-inch) muffin cups with foil baking cups or place on cookie sheet.
Combine brownie mix, fudge packet from mix, eggs, water and oil in large bowl. Stir with spoon until well blended, about 50 strokes.
Place 1 level measuring spoon of batter in each foil liner.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Push 1 peanut butter cup candy in center of each cupcake until even with surface of brownie.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl. Add beaten egg and milk to cornmeal mixture. Mix in onion and Tabasco. Drop by heaping teaspoons into hot fat
(375°) and fry until brown. Drain and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and Crisco.
Add vanilla and water, then pumpkin.
Mix other dry ingredients together and add to pumpkin mixture.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with corn chips.
Especially nice in summer.

title: hardy's biscuits
directions: Sift first four ingredients together; cut in shortening and slowly add buttermilk.
(If dough is too soft, add little more flour before kneading.)
Pat or roll out to 3/4-inch thick.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes 15 medium size biscuits.
(Place pan of biscuits in middle of oven to bake a more uniform biscuit.)
Brush tops with butter after removing from oven.

title: egg casserole
directions: Place cubed bread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with pre-fried, cubed sausage and cheese.
Blend eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over bread, cheese and sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together (at room temperature) the Velveeta cheese and cream cheese.
Add paste from juice of lemon, garlic and sugar. Mix together thoroughly with cheese mixture.
Add pecans.
Mix again.
Roll in a ball or log.
(Serve with crackers.) Refrigerate.

title: gourmet crab ring
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water to soften. Stir over hot water until dissolved. Beat into cream cheese until smooth. Stir in next 5 ingredients and 2 tablespoons of the parsley. Pour into a 3-cup ring mold. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until set.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.
Saute onion in oleo.
Mix all remaining ingredients in bowl using only half the cheese.
Cut artichokes in half; place into greased 11 x 7-inch casserole.
Pour spinach mixture over the artichoke halves. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom chicken rice
directions: Mix rice and 2 cans of soup.
Place in casserole dish.
Place leg quarters on top. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: jerry's hot barbecue beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon in a large pot and set aside. Fry bacon very, very crisp.
Add bacon and all of the grease to the other ingredients.
Bring to a very slow boil.
Reduce heat to maintain a slow boil for 1 hour.
Stir from bottom about every 6 to 8 minutes to prevent sticking.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients for 6 minutes.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Put half of batter into greased pan; put half of nut mixture over batter.
Add remaining batter and mixture. Bake at 350° until done.
Poke holes in warm cake with fork; pour thin frosting over.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Reserve 4 cookies for topping.
Using large glass bowl, layer ingredients as follows:

1/2 package of cookies (crumbled into bottom of bowl), little bit of chocolate syrup, 1/2 package of chocolate chips, 1/2 of walnuts, 2 sliced bananas, 1/2 bottle chocolate syrup and 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Repeat pattern to finish ingredients.
Top with 4 crushed cookies and maraschino cherries.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Cut the chicken wings in two at the joints.
In a large frying pan or skillet, heat to 360° enough oil to fry until crisp, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken in the microwave
directions: Mix melted butter and A.1. sauce.
Place fryer in a microwave safe dish with cover, breast side down.
Brush top of fryer with mixture; cover with lid and microwave on High for 15 minutes. Turn fryer, coat breast side with mixture and microwave on High for another 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Let cool.
Slice cake in half crosswise.
Mix Cool Whip, oranges, pudding and crushed pineapple in bowl.
Mix well.
Place filling between layers and on top.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in order given in a large pot and bake for 3 hours at 350°, covered.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese with remaining ingredients and cook on low heat for 30 minutes in crock-pot.
Serve with chips.

title: gourmet chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice
in
a
well-greased long casserole.
Mix soups, butter, milk,
sherry and seasoning mix that is in rice package. Pour small	amount	on
rice.
Place chicken on rice and add remaining
liquid
mix.
Sprinkle almond and cheese on top or cheese and	paprika.
Bake	at
for
2 1/2 hours, uncovered. Do not stir during baking.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Combine soups, broth, tomatoes and green chilies; blend until smooth.
Place a layer of chicken in a casserole dish.
Add layers of tortillas, onion, cheese and sauce.
Repeat layers, ending in cheese (about 3 layers).
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato au gratin
directions: Cook and dice potatoes.
Make white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese until it is melted and well mixed.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef with onions and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix, bake until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Pour rice in dish.
Place chicken over rice.
Mix mushroom soup, onion soup mix and water. Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
tags: cream of chicken soup with mushrooms

title: fruit noodle pudding
directions: To plump raisins, soak them in juice for 1 hour or overnight. Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles in the boiling water 5 to 10 minutes until tender.
Place noodles, margarine, apples and raisins in a large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar and bake for 45 minutes until top is brown and crisp.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot or cold.

title: ranch dressing cheese ball
directions: Combine Ranch dressing mix, mayonnaise and milk.
Mix well. (This will actually make a double strength salad dressing.)
Use 1/2 cup of this dressing mix and blend with cream cheese.
Beat well with electric mixer.
Add Cheddar cheese and blend.
Cover and freeze for 30 minutes.
Shape cheese mixture into ball.
Roll cheese ball in roasted almonds.

title: homemade soup
directions: Add beans, peas, carrots and potatoes to 1 quart of water and boil until tender.
Add to other ingredients in large pot and cook for 30 minutes. While boiling hot, put in jars and seal.
Makes 12 quarts.

title: pork and noodle casserole
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Cook pork, celery, pepper and onion until the meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
In a large bowl, combine pork mixture, noodles, soups, corn, milk, salt and pepper; mix well.
Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: home-canned tomato juice (v-8 style)
directions: Blanch, peel, core and quarter tomatoes. Puree in food processor. Bring tomatoes to simmer. Add spices and sugar. Simmer until tomatoes turn color and quit smelling like tomatoes. Put through water bath for 40 minutes. Yields approximately 10 quarts.

title: wassail punch
directions: In a large pan, mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Serve warm.
Put Pomander Ball in punch bowl with punch.

title: dairy orange salad
directions: Pour the boiling water over Jell-O.
Add marshmallows and stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Defrost orange juice and stir in 1/2 cup sugar.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Cream the cheese and add the pineapple to cheese.
Add this to the Jell-O mixture.
Next, add the cottage cheese, bananas and orange sections.
Stir until well mixed.
Finally, stir in whipped cream.
Pour in large container. Place in refrigerator for at least 3 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until tender in the water.
Add soup and cheese. Simmer.

title: spanish potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes, then pour mixture over 6 medium, hot, peeled, diced and cooked potatoes.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cool 'n easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin until dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into gelatin until thickened. Remove ice.
Stir in whipped topping.
Refrigerate 10 minutes. Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate four hours.
Garnish with whipped topping.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine strawberries and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover and let stand in the refrigerator at least 1 hour.
In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, baking powder and baking soda. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture all at once, stirring until combined.
Spray 8-inch round baking pan with nonstick spray coating.
With lightly floured hands, pat dough into pan.
Bake in a 450° oven about 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely, or serve warm.

title: barbecued chicken(serves 4)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, in a saucepan and whisk together over moderate heat.
Cool.
Sauce may be refrigerated until needed (it will keep for at least 10 days) or use as soon as it has cooled.

title: fish chowder
directions: Simmer fish with water for 5 minutes or until fish can be flaked. Remove fish. Boil fish broth 10 minutes or until reduced to about 1 2/3 cups. Remove skin, unless you buy skinless haddock and cool fish. Saut onions in 5 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in flour. Gradually add fish broth. Add potatoes, celery, seasonings and about 2/3 cup of fish. Simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Scald milk. Remove from heat. Add cream and sour cream. (Bring the cream and sour cream to room temperature or they'll curdle.) Beat with a wire whip until creams are well combined. Reheat slowly; don't boil. Add potatoes and fish mixture to the milk mixture. Heat 5 minutes. Remove loose bay leaves. Top with butter. Best heated next day. Makes 3 quarts.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt.
Cook over high heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add pecans.
