Continue stirring until ball stage.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: springerle(christmas cookies)
directions: Beat
eggs 10 minutes at high speed.
Add confectioners sugar gradually
to
eggs.
Beat, then add Crisco oil, flour, baking powder,
salt and anise extract.
Chill good and cold. Roll out with form roller and cut.
Place on cookie sheets or board.
Let stand overnight (uncovered).
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix the sugar and vinegar.
Add enough mayonnaise to make a dressing.
Cover the chopped ingredients.

title: baked chicken and peas
directions: Pour peas into casserole dish or long pan.
Layer chicken pieces on top of peas.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix chicken soup with enough water to spread over chicken.
Cover with foil. Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 400° oven.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook rice; wash and drain.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Saute onion in oleo.
Mix soup, milk and cheese until smooth.
Add onion and oleo.
In buttered 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/2 rice, 1/2 broccoli and 1/2 sauce.
Repeat.
Cover with fried onion rings or bread crumbs.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and lemon juice.
Chill 1 hour.
Add grapes and almonds.
Combine rest of ingredients. Add chicken and toss.

title: squash pickles
directions: Cut onions and squash; put in large pan and let set for 1 hour.
Add all other ingredients; bring to a boil in a different pan.
Then pour over squash and onions.
Let come to a hard boil; pour in jars and seal.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook meats together; drain.
Add soup, Ro-Tel and picante sauce.
Cut Velveeta cheese in chunks, then melt.
Combine all ingredients together.
Serve with chips.

title: carrot yogurt cake
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Beat in sugar and eggs.
Mix with lemon peel, cinnamon, vanilla and yogurt and cream.
Stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add this to creamed mixture, beating until smooth.
Mix pecans and carrots into mixture.
Turn into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown and inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool.
Makes 16 servings.

title: polish cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage thin.
Place in bowl.
Slice onions very thin into rings.
Sprinkle parsley over cabbage.
Mix all ingredients and chill until ready to serve.
Mix oil and vinegar in a jar and shake well (oil and vinegar mix better if shaken together before adding sugar).
Add sugar, again shake the ingredients together. After mixing well, chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together, adding butter last, and crumbling Ritz crackers on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dandy don's tuna
directions: Drain tuna, then add eggs, celery, apple, onion, relish and pecans.
Add mayonnaise last; mix well.
Serve cold.

title: bridal soup
directions: Combine ground chuck, salt, pepper, parsley, 2 Tbsp. Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs. Form into balls size of a grape; set aside.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Put syrup, sugar and water into a saucepan.
Boil until mixture is a light golden color.
Stir in the butter and cream. Remove from heat but keep warm.
Serves 8.

title: crunch salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Just before serving, stir in potato stix.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan, well-greased.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: country apple prune cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Blend in apples.
Combine dry ingredients and gradually beat into egg mixture.
Stir in prunes and nuts.
Spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack to cool.
Just before serving, dust cake with confectioners sugar.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add cocoa alternately with milk, beating it smooth. Gradually add whipping cream, beating until stiff.
Spoon into crust.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with freshly grated chocolate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creole venison stew
directions: Layer vegetables in a large kettle.
Cut venison in cubes and place on top of vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to the pot.
Add water until liquid is visible around the meat. Simmer, covered, for 8 hours.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla on medium speed for 10 minutes.
Place a vanilla wafer on the bottom of muffin tin lined with cupcake papers. Pour filling in each one, 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Top with pie filling or jam.
For a bigger batch, use 3 packages of cream cheese and 2/3 cup sugar.

title: baked spaghetti with cheese
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish put a layer of spaghetti.
Top all over with dots of butter.
Cover with grated cheese and continue layers like this until pan is full.
Pour evaporated milk from can until saturated.
Bake in 325° oven 20 to 30 minutes until milk has absorbed.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix mashed bananas, orange juice and lemonade.
Dissolve sugar in 2 cups water over fire.
Add to mixture.
Add pineapple juice and freeze.
Thaw 1 1/2 hours and serve with 2 quarts ginger ale. Mix in punch bowl with wooden spoon.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, crumble and set aside.
Place all ingredients, except cheese and meat, in blender and mix a few seconds to blend well.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle cheese and meat over top and gently push below surface. Pie pan will be full to the rim.
It will form its own crust in baking.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with beef slices and secure with 1/2 strip of bacon (can fasten with toothpicks).
Place in shallow baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: jane's luscious lime mold
directions: Mix sour cream and crushed pineapple and juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add to sour cream and pineapple. Refrigerate until jelled.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Make into balls. Brown and drain.
Put a thin layer of spahetti sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Add meatballs, top with mushrooms, and Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serve with noodles.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat ingredients together. Pour into lightly baked pie shell and bake for 10 minutes. Garnish with whipped topping and lime curls.

title: hawaiian tropical pie
directions: Line pan with crust.
Layer with sliced bananas.
Mix lemon juice and milk.
Pour over bananas.
Spread pineapple on next, then Cool Whip, coconut and pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together and store until ready to use.

title: "hot" taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of dish.
Top with chili, then salsa.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or microwave on High 5 minutes (must be turntable).
Dip nacho chips and enjoy!

title: beans & rice enchiladas
directions: Cook beans and rice according to package omitting margarine. Preheat oven to 350°.
In a skillet, brown onions and peppers in oil.
Add to beans and rice.
In each tortilla spoon 1/3 cup of beans and rice.
Roll up and place on oven proof casserole dish. Pour salsa over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream
together
first 4 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients, mixing alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick tests clean.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out.

title: lemon coconut bars
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Press evenly in 8-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Meanwhile, beat eggs until thick and lemon colored and gradually beat in sugar. Add pudding and baking powder, then dates and coconut.
Spread on hot crust.
Return to oven.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until puffed and browned.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes about 18 bars.

title: chunky cabbage salad
directions: Mix in large bowl chopped cabbage and onions (chopped fine). Brown almonds, sesame seed, sunflower seeds and noodles.
Just before serving, toss together with dressing.
Dressing is the vinegar, oil and sugar and seasoning from noodles mix.

title: pheasant casserole
directions: Parboil pheasant for 10 minutes.
Take all meat off bones and set aside.
Cook rice and remaining ingredients, except mushrooms and sour cream.
When all the liquid is absorbed, add sour cream and mushrooms.
Mix well.

title: basic stir-fry
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and ginger.
Toss with soy sauce and set aside to marinate.

title: peach chutney
directions: Pour boiling water over peaches; let stand until skins can be easily removed.
Dip in cold water; peel.
Remove pits and red fibers; cut into chunks.
Place immediately in vinegar-water to prevent browning.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar and next 4 ingredients.
Add cloves and cinnamon tied in cheesecloth bag. Drain peaches; add to syrup.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove spice bag.
Continue simmering while quickly packing one clean hot jar at a time.
Fill to within 1/2-inch of top, making sure syrup covers fruit.
Seal each jar at once. Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 4 to 5 half pints.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over the oats. Let stand while mixing the remaining ingredients. Now, add the oats and blend well. Cook in baking pan, 8 x 12 x 3-inch sides. Bake at 300° about 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Toast bread lightly; butter generously.
Cut into about 1/4 inch squares.
Arrange in buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with raisins.

title: fast fixin cake(chocolate)
directions: Pour oil in 13-inch cake; tilt pan to cover bottom.
Put in remaining ingredients and stir with fork until all ingredients are mixed.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Ground nuts may be sprinkled on top before baking, if wanted.

title: spiced pear jam
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until thick, stirring occasionally.
Stir more frequently as mixture thickens.
Remove from the heat; skim off foam.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps.
Process for 10 minutes in a boiling water bath. Yields 6 half pints.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Pour evaporated milk into a medium-size bowl and whip with an electric mixer until soft peaks form, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix water, lemon juice and gelatin in microwave bowl and heat on High for 1 minute.
Stir to dissolve gelatin; mix whipped milk, sugar, food coloring and gelatin mixture with an electric mixer until thoroughly blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with inverted plastic dome and chill until fully set, at least 1 hour.
Garnish with fruit, if desired.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and flour (add egg one at a time).
Fold in 7-Up and flavoring.
(Don't stir too much.) Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Grease and flour pan.

title: hot sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Remove sausage from casings; cook in large skillet, breaking up the meat with a fork, until no longer pink, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain off fat; spoon sausage into large bowl.
Cool completely.
Add cheese, biscuit mix and water; mix with a fork just until blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls; place on large cookie sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until puffed and browned.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool completely on wire racks.

title: big batch cookies
directions: Cook raisins in as little water as possible, then cool.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in corn oil until tender. Add ground chuck and cook until meat browns. Stir constantly. Remove from fire. Add remaining ingredients and cook in 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Pretzels should not be crushed too fine.
Allow some very small pieces to remain for crunch.
A good way to crush them is to put pretzels into strong plastic bag and press firmly with rolling pin. Mix together pretzel crumbs, margarine and sugar and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for JUST eight minutes, NO LONGER! Let cool.
Beat cream cheese with 1 cup sugar until well combined. Stir in Cool Whip and spread on cooled pretzel crust.
Dissolve jello in boiling water, then stir in frozen strawberries.
Let this mixture stand for 10 minutes.
Pour on top of cheese mixture and chill.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry the bacon strips, then brown onion in those drippings. Then brown ground beef until done.
Drain off excess grease.
Add sprinkle of salt.
Set aside.
Into large bowl or pan, put pork and beans.
Add mustard, sorghum or Karo, brown sugar and catsup or barbecue sauce.
(Catsup is the preference of the writer.) Stir and mix into the meat mixture.
Place the bacon strips on top and bake one hour at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together; spoon into hot cooking oil.
(I use my Fry Daddy. They seem to be much lighter.)

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a bowl, mix pineapple, flour and sugar. Stir in cheese and pour into a buttered casserole dish. Mix crackers and margarine. Put on top of other ingredients. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Arrange lettuce on four individual plates.
Mix rices and all vegetables except asparagus.
Arrange in mound in center of lettuce.
Use one asparagus, one shrimp, one scallop and one lobster tail per plate.
Drizzle with dressing and serve.

title: christmas wassail
directions: *You may also use the juice that comes in the small plastic containers at vegetable markets.

title: herbed bread
directions: Cut loaf in 1/2 horizontally.
Blend butter and salad dressing mix.
Spread on bread.
Wrap bread in foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: herb garden chicken salad
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven (large pot); add water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add potatoes; cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Cool; drain.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Press down and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool completely. Mix next 3 ingredients together and spread on pastry.
Whip next 3 ingredients and spread on first layer.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle grated Heath or chocolate bar on top.
Chill until firm.

title: millionaires pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice; add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add pineapple and chopped nuts.
Pour into graham cracker crusts. Keep refrigerated overnight before serving.

title: impossible lasagna pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: With wire whisk, beat sugar, oil and vinegar.
Add onion and poppy seed.
Will keep for weeks in refrigerator.

title: rave reviews cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Blend; beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased, floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 65 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool on rack.

title: refrigerator crescent rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 c. flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Saute 1/2 cup finely chopped onion in one tablespoon margarine until tender.
Add to rest of ingredients and mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons of margarine, then pour one can cream of mushroom soup over meat balls.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
(Thicken slightly for gravy.)

title: peanut jumbles
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, peanut butter, sugars and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients and peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: trail mix
directions: Mix all and put in a bowl or decorative jar to serve.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Season chops.
Place in large skillet.
Cover with rice, green pepper and onion; season with salt and pepper.
Combine water and catsup; pour over chops and bring to a boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in coconut, dates, raisins and nuts.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into balls. Place 1/2 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Put 1/2 cup onions and 1/2 cup cheese with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then sprinkle with remaining onions and cheese.
Return to oven for 5 more minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; set aside.
Bring margarine, shortening, cocoa and water to a rapid boil.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour in greased 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes first 7 ingredients.
Cool and gradually add sifted flour and soda.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: caballero casserole
directions: Set oven to 400°.
Cut each tamale into 6 slices and place half in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with 1 can of corn. Top with remaining tamale slices and corn.
Pour pizza sauce over all. Now see recipe for Cheese Olive Topping.

title: short pie tart shells
directions: Heat oven to 450° (hot).
Blend Bisquick and butter in bowl. Add boiling water and stir vigorously with fork until dough forms a ball and cleans the bowl.
Dough will be puffy and soft.
Divide into 6 parts.
Pat out each piece on a 5 inch circle of heavy-duty aluminum foil (use lid of coffee can to measure foil).
Makes tart shells by folding up an inch of foil and pinching in 4 corners. Place tarts on baking sheets.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.
Remove foil carefully.

title: sweet 'n sour hot dogs
directions: To make appetizer, thread 1 hot dog chunk, 1 green pepper square and 1 pineapple chunk on each toothpick.
Set aside. Combine ketchup and grape jelly in a 10-inch skillet or electric frypan with Silverstone.
Heat until jelly melts and mixture boils.
Stir in peach flavored brandy.
Add appetizers.
Cover and simmer over low heat, about 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 12 as hors d'oeuvres.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Microwave bacon on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Heat onion and celery in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings on High, 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Add shrimp, heat on high for 2 to 3 minutes or until shrimp are pink.
Add remaining ingredients; toss until well mixed.
Bacon drippings may be eliminated and sunflower oil used. If using peas, add at same time as shrimp.

title: chicken pie casserole
directions: Mix soup, broth and vegetables.
Layer baking dish with boiled chicken.
Pour soup, broth and vegetables over chicken.
Mix flour, milk, butter and sugar.
Pour over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken with salt, pepper and butter in a 3-quart pot until chicken is tender.

title: peanut butterscotch drops
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces and peanut butter together over low heat.
Add cereal and peanuts; stir until evenly coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper and chill.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in seasonings and tomato sauce. Simmer slowly for 20 minutes.
Prepare 1/2 package Creamettes lasagna according to package directions.
Drain. Arrange one layer of lasagna in parallel strips in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with 1/3 of the meat mixture and 1/3 of the cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: nell's easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Add all ingredients in large skillet, simmer for 30 minutes.

title: fried pickles
directions: Preheat oil to frying temperature.
Depending on preference, cut pickles lengthwise or crosswise making sure that slices are kept rather thin.
Place pickles in bowl and set aside to let juices drain partially.
Mix batter, cayenne pepper, creole seasoning and beer in large mixing bowl.
Dip pickle slices into batter and fry until golden brown.

title: maine baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
On the next morning, parboil until skins crack when blown upon.
Add salt pork.
Mix sugar, molasses, mustard, pepper and salt into 1 pint of boiling water.
Pour this over beans and pork.
If necessary, add more boiling water to cover.
Add more water when needed while baking. Bake at 300° for 6 hours.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Rub hot skillet with suet; add meat and sear on both sides. Push to one side.
Rub skillet again with suet; add remaining ingredients.
Cook over high heat for about 3 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 to 7 minutes more.
Stir gently several times.
Vegetables should be crisp.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Add salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Stir well to mix.
Layer 1/2 of meat mixture with chips and cheese.
Top with other half of meat.
Add chips and end with cheese on top.
Also good with lettuce and tomato on top.

title: crab crisps
directions: Preheat broiler. Drain and flake crab. Combine crab, sour cream, cheese and onion soup.
Place about 1 tablespoon on each toast round and spread to the edges with a spatula.
Place rounds on a cookie sheet. Broil about 4-inches from broiler for 4 or 5 minutes or until tops are bubbly and lightly browned.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine corn, eggs and milk.
Pour into a buttered casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 4 generous servings.
If recipe is doubled, increase baking time to 1 hour.

title: dusty potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Combine bread crumbs, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Dip potatoes in melted butter; roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place in greased jelly roll pan or on a cookie sheet with sides.
Bake until crisp and brown, about 1 hour, at 350°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 10-inch round pans.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix and Jell-O together. With mixer at low speed, add vegetable oil and milk.
Turn mixer to medium speed.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in strawberries, pecans and coconut.
Pour batter in pans and bake for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool layers in pan or wire rack 10 minutes.

title: strawberry treats
directions: Mix and chill for 1 hour.
Shape to resemble strawberries. Roll in red sugar.

title: mincemeat(canned)
directions: Mix ingredients and cook slow in large dish pan or slow cooker until raisins are puffed and seem dry.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Can hot in hot, dry jars.
Seal at once.
Makes 6 quarts.
Other fruits can be added.

title: angel food cake
directions: Cut cake in half.
Put half a can of pudding in center.
Mix rest of pudding with Cool Whip and frost cake.

title: broccoli stuffing casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and stuffing according to instructions.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, onions and eggs in a mixing bowl and mix until smooth.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
In 2-quart casserole dish, layer 1/2 broccoli, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 stuffing, 1/2 butter, 1/2 soup. Repeat for 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 2nd place: tropical bread
directions: Mix and
sift
flour,
sugar,
baking
powder and salt. Stir in coconut.
Combine milk, egg and vanilla and add to dry ingredients.
Stir	well.
Blend
in
dates
and apples.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chili-cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips.
Heat, stirring occasionally, over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve heated with chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: monterey shrimp dip
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients in a 1-quart microwave-safe dish. Microwave at High 3 minutes or until cheese melts, stirring after each minute. Serve immediately with tortilla chips. Yield: 3 1/4 cups.

title: turkey and asparagus casserole
directions: Cook asparagus according to package directions; drain. Arrange asparagus in an 8-inch square baking pan.
Place turkey slices on asparagus.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and
curry powder and pour over turkey.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Mix egg, oil, and buttermilk together in bowl.
Add flour. Dissolve baking soda in water, then add to mixture.
Stir briskly but not too long.
Pour mixture onto waffle grill.
Cook until light brown.
Top with butter while hot.
Makes two waffles.

title: zesty hot sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve with fish or seafood.
Makes 1 3/4 cups sauce.

title: spinach salad
directions: Clean spinach thoroughly, use leaves only.
Dry leaves; hull and wash strawberries.
Slice each strawberry in half.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent dough into a 15 x 10-inch baking sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 375° or until brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill, garlic and onion.
Spread on crust.
Sprinkle with veggies.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: no bake lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemonade and Eagle Brand milk until smooth. Pour mixture into pie shell.
Chill until firm.

title: barbecued sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, stir.
Use with meatballs.

title: garlic new potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Saute garlic in butter in a small skillet until tender.
Add parsley and pepper to skillet.
Pour mixture over potatoes, tossing gently to coat.

title: wassail
directions: Mix this with first four ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: coconut pie
directions: For crust, mix oil, milk, salt and flour together.
Pat into pie pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.

title: tuna potato pie
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Add flour, stirring until smooth. Add milk slowly.
Stir all the time until mixture is bubbly. Reduce heat and cook 3 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, tuna, peas and onions.
Continue cooking until onions soften.
Place in baking dish. Top with mashed potatoes, dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until top is brown.

title: glowing lime green punch
directions: Dissolve powdered drink in the pineapple juice.
Add scoops of lime sherbet and the ginger ale just before serving.
Yield: 25 servings.
Garnish with fruit slices.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Slice carrots.
Cook and drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Serve cold.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Cool.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: cantaloupe congealed salad
directions: Slice cantaloupe in half and remove seeds.
Scoop melon balls from cantaloupe and mix with jello which has been prepared according to package directions.
Fill cantaloupe cavity with jello mixture and let congeal.
Rest cantaloupe in a small Tupperware bowl to keep from tilting in refrigerator.
When congealed, cut halves into quarters and serve with crackers. Yields 4 servings.

title: chapattis
directions: Mix thoroughly, the flour, salt and oil.
Add enough water to make a soft bread-like dough.
Divide into 8 balls and roll out thin; it will be about 8 inches in diameter.
Bake on a hot griddle or skillet a few minutes on each side.
May be spread with margarine and filled with rice, beans or any desired filling and rolled up, or eaten as is.
Makes 8 Chapattis.

title: i-45 min. cream cheese cake
directions: Combine melted butter, egg and cake mix. Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine softened cream cheese, eggs, brown sugar, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt. Beat until smooth. Spread cream cheese mixture over cake mixture. Bake in preheated 325° oven about 45 minutes or until cake is golden brown on top. Cut into small squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mexican fireballs
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except cheese; mix well.
Form 1-inch balls.
Stuff each with either the olives, pineapple, water chestnuts or mushrooms.
Coat the balls with Parmesan cheese. Place them on a baking tray; bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes. May be frozen before baking.
Makes 40 appetizers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello; add cranberries, apples, oranges and pineapple.
Let set.

title: can't miss casserole
directions: In a greased 2-quart baking dish, combine rice, salt, pepper, corn, 1 can tomato sauce, water, onion and green pepper.
Add ground beef and second can of tomato sauce.
Add 1/4 can of water and cover with bacon strips.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake for 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot ham and cheese appetizers
directions: Mix butter, mustard and onion; refrigerate overnight.
Cut ham and cheese into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Spread both sides of each dinner roll with butter mixture.
Put 2 to 3 squares of ham and 1 square of cheese onto each roll.
Wrap each roll in a small piece of foil.
At this point the rolls can be frozen until further use or baked in a 350° oven for 15 minutes, until heated through and cheese is melted.
If baking frozen rolls, adjust baked time by 5 to 7 minutes.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Stir in egg, molasses and vinegar.
Beat
well.
Sift dry ingredients; stir in.
Chill 3 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Beat eggs, add milk, salt and mustard. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Place in a cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Melt butter.
Add bread crumbs.
Butter baking dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Add half the apples, then sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Repeat, having top layer of bread crumbs.
Cover dish and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove cover and let crumbs brown.

title: sticky chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off chicken wings and cut in 2 pieces.
Mix ingredients.
Pour over wings.
Marinate 24 hours.
Spread out on cookie sheet in one layer.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not add any of the sauce when baking.

title: savory popcorn
directions: Mix well, then try any of the following additions:

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in loaf pan or baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: long john silver's fish batter
directions: Beat eggs and spices together.
Add enough flour to form a stiff dough (like pastry dough).
Add beer, mixing thoroughly. Keep adding beer until dough is thin and smooth.
Dip fish in flour, then in batter, then fry in deep oil.

title: marinated veggies
directions: Drain and wash canned veggies in colander.
Place all ingredients in large, airtight container.

title: scalloped potatoes in cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and seasonings.
Stir until smooth. Slowly add hot milk, stirring.
When thickened, melt cheese in sauce.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients first in large container with tight fitting lid.
Add liquids and mix well.
To bake, fill muffin cups or paper liners 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
This keeps well in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: baked chocolate pudding
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift with salt, sugar, baking powder and cocoa.
Combine with melted butter, vanilla and milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add nuts and pour into large buttered baking dish; cover with Cocoa Mix. Pour the water over all and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ham and potato supper
directions: Place butter in heated skillet to melt.
Add the sliced potatoes and place the ham steaks over this.
Cover and set on low to medium setting for 1 hour.
There's no need for salt on the potatoes because the flavor from the ham drains down onto them and flavors them greatly.

title: toffee fantasy pie
directions: Place milk and pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat with wire whip until well blended, about 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes. Set aside 1/4 cup toffee bits.
Gently fold remaining toffee bits and whipped topping into pudding.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Sprinkle with reserved toffee bits.
Freeze at least 6 hours. Remove from freezer; let stand 10 minutes to soften before serving.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a medium casserole dish at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican pasta toss
directions: In a large bowl, combine shells, beans and corn.
Toss with salsa and garnish with grated cheese.
Serve cold.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Prepare first 4 ingredients; mix together with Miracle Whip and garnish with maraschino cherries.
Use a little lemon juice on apples to keep them white if not serving immediately.

title: mashed potatoes plus
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Mash potatoes, then add remaining items.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour if refrigerated.
If baked as made, bake for 30 minutes.

title: nacho potato soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan combine the contents of the potato package, corn, tomatoes and water; mix well.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, cheese and hot pepper sauce (if desired).
Cook and stir until the cheese is melted.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings (2 quarts).

title: breakfast crunch
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Heat the milk; add molasses. Mix with dry ingredients.
Bake in shallow pan in moderate oven. Grind and toast like grapenuts.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover with milk until soggy. Cover dish and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
If still too soggy, take cover off.
Cook for a few more minutes.

title: homemade apple butter
directions: Cook at 350 degrees for 3 1/2 hours; stir about every half hour. Cook in dishpan about 3/4 from top of oven.

title: potato soup with ham
directions: Boil potatoes slowly in water until tender.
Do not drain; add butter.
Add soup gradually, stirring until smooth.
Stir in salt, pepper and ham.
Cook for 10 minutes longer.
Serve with soda crackers.
Yields 5 servings.

title: easy hot broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over med. heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated. Yields about 1 quart.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Mix all ingredients with a mixer and pour into dish.

title: grandma jennie's chicken soup
directions: Place chopped vegetables and water in a large pot and boil. Add chicken.
Boil until chicken is soft.
Take the chicken out of the water and remove from the bone; then put back in the pot.
Add peppercorns, bay leaf, salt as well as the tortellini.
Serve when tortellini are cooked.

title: beef log
directions: Mix well. Roll in 1/2-inch rolls (this makes about 5 rolls). Wrap tightly in plastic wrap. Store in refrigerator for 24 hours; place on broiler pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool. Keep refrigerated or frozen.

title: nutty puppies
directions: Combine ingredients well; roll into 36 one-ounce rolls. Fry in 450° deep fat until golden brown. Serve with seafood.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine. Add rice and soup. Stir. Bake in casserole (uncovered) at 350° about 1 hour.

title: company's comin' chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken in salt water until tender.
When chicken is good and done, remove from salt water.
Cut into bite-size pieces.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine margarine, milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Stir.
Beat until marshmallows blend.
Pour in buttered pan.
Cool.

title: crab mystery salad
directions: Thaw and dice crabmeat.
Remove crust from bread and cut in 3/8-inch cubes.
Combine all ingredients but add crabmeat last. Stir.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Serve in bowl with lettuce leaves arranged on bottom.

title: berry pie
directions: Melt butter in a 5 x 9-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour over melted butter.
Sprinkle berries over mix.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Cook one whole hen in large pan on top of stove.
Add water continuously as it boils and evaporates.
Salt hen.
Cook for about 4 hours or until tender.
Remove from pot and brown in oven. Dip out 1 cup of broth from cooking pan.
Set broth aside until it is cool, but still warm.
Mix in flour, soda, baking powder and salt until dough has a biscuit-like consistency.
Knead and roll out 1/4-inch thick on floured board.
Cut in strips until dumpling pieces are about 2 x 2-inches.
Bring remaining broth in cooking pan to a boil.
Drop dumplings in one at a time.
Cook until tender with a fork.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in the milk (heat, but do not boil).
Mix other ingredients together.
Add the marshmallow-milk mixture last.
Pack mixture into lined pans.
Cover with foil; leave in refrigerator overnight.
This will keep for several days, even weeks.
Serve in small pieces, as it is rich.

title: cheese bread
directions: Grease loaf pan and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of corn meal. In a saucepan, combine milk, sugar, salt and butter.
Heat until butter melts.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese in mixer until smooth.
Add sour cream and sugar; mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into balls.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Chill until served.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jacques and suzanne vinaigrette salad sauce(3 cups)
directions: *Five-eighths cup equals 1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then cool.

title: orange-pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl and stir well.
Churn in ice cream churn.

title: apple relish
directions: Attach food grinder, using coarse grinding plate.
Turn to speed 4 and grind onions and red pepper in small bowl.
Add water and salt.
Let stand 15 minutes, then drain.
Attach clean grinder with coarse plate.
Grind apples into a 5-quart pot.
Add onion and red pepper mixture, vinegar, sugar and cloth bag filled with spices.
Bring to a boil and cook 15 minutes.
Remove spice bag.

title: chocolate pecan fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, cocoa, Karo and oleo to a soft ball stage when dropped in a cup of water.
Remove from heat.
Beat with beater until mixture thickens.
Add Marshmallow Creme, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased oblong pan.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: baked cheese potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 15-inch Pyrex pan.
Pare and quarter enough potatoes to completely cover the bottom of the pan.
Roll over in butter as placing in the pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Grate cheese and mix with crumbled bread and paprika.
Sprinkle over the top of the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german meat loaf
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Bake in a loaf pan or round casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Place bacon strips (uncooked) on top of formed loaf before putting in oven if you so desire.

title: asparagus rice casserole
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour, and milk.
Add 1/3 of the cheese and stir until melted.
In a deep casserole dish, arrange layers of rice, asparagus, eggs, and sauce.
Put rest of cheese on top with some crackers crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Place 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cupcake paper liner.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring often. Reduce to medium heat. Cook 20 minutes. Remove from heat. Add vanilla.

title: stambouli's moussaka
directions: Peel potatoes; cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown; drain.
Arrange half of potatoes in an even layer in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Saute onions in oil; set aside.
In remaining oil, cook beef; stir with a fork until all redness is gone.
Add onions, garlic, tomato sauce, cinnamon and salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Arrange remaining potato slices over meat.
Beat eggs into white sauce.
Pour over meat and potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sue's white choco party mix
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double broiler.
Mix remaining ingredients in large pan.
Pour melted chocolate over pan contents. Cover cookie sheets or counter top with wax paper.
Spread out mixture to dry (approximately 1 1/2 hours).

title: fernandez's extreme nachos
directions: On a large platter, place a layer of chips, followed by lettuce, quartered tomato and sliced onion.
Slice and saute one onion and the green pepper; set aside.
Brown and drain the hamburger.
Mix the hamburger with refried beans and heat.
Spoon the hamburger-refried bean mix over the chips and vegetables. Place the sauteed onion and green pepper over the hamburger-refried beans.
Cover with green chilies, black olives and cheese.
Broil until the cheese melts.
Garnish with hot peppers; start dipping into your favorite salsa (mine is made with habanera peppers).
Be sure to have plenty of Mexican beer around!!

title: cream cheese crescents
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese, creaming until well blended. Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Shape dough
into 8 balls. Wrap each in plastic wrap and chill at least 2 hours. Roll each ball of dough into an 8-inch circle on a lightly floured surface. Cut into wedges.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add parsley, celery salt and salt and pepper (to taste).
Drain off excess fat.
Layer meat mixture in bottom of casserole.
Layer with mashed potatoes.
Do this until casserole is full.
When making potatoes, use water instead of milk.
Bake at 300° until heated through.
Very good.

title: pearl's special mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients except cheese. Pour 1/2 batter into a large greased iron skillet.
Arrange cheese slices on top; cover cheese completely with remaining batter. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until golden.

title: "sugar cookies"
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour. Slowly add flour and mix together thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until soft. Dough will seem sticky. Cut about 1/4-inch thick.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: crab mold
directions: Melt cream of mushroom soup with cream cheese in saucepan. Mix cold water with gelatin.
Add to mixture in saucepan.
Remove from heat; drain crab and mix with celery and onion.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix all together.
Refrigerate in mold and serve with crackers.

title: tea punch
directions: This punch is based on flavored gelatin, which allows you to choose the color to blend with party decorations.
In large quantities, additions of food coloring may be necessary to have a bright color.
Freeze some of the punch in ice cubes or a ring mold with pieces of fruit and mint for decoration.
This punch also can serve as a starter for adding many additional flavors such as sherbet.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
For a less sweet taste substitute some or all club soda.
May be made the day before serving.
Double as desired.

title: southern colonel fried chicken
directions: Mix pancake mix and 1 package salad dressing (both dry); set aside.
Beat egg with water; stir in second package salad dressing (dry).
Coat evenly each piece of cut up chicken with egg-water-dressing mixture, then roll in pancake-dressing mix. Let dry on toweling.
Heat 1-inch deep oil in a heavy skillet (400°).
Fry 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Place on cookie sheets in 350° oven for 30 minutes for crispy coating.

title: 40 clove garlic chicken
directions: Brush chicken pieces on all sides with oil.
In a large casserole or baking dish, combine the onion, celery, parsley and tarragon.
Arrange the chicken pieces on top and pour the vermouth over the chicken.
Sprinkle the chicken with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Distribute the unpeeled garlic cloves throughout the casserole, tucking them under and around the chicken.
Cover top of pan or dish tightly with foil.
Bake the chicken in a preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours; no peeking.
Do not uncover for 1 1/2 hours!
Serve the chicken over rice with the garlic.
The garlic cloves can be squeezed over Melba toast.
Serves 4.

title: juicy julius drink
directions: You will need a blender filled halfway with small ice cubes (2 cups).

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a plastic bag.
Shake to mix well.
Brush both sides with buttermilk.
Place in bag of crumbs and shake to coat.
Place chicken in pan that has been sprayed with vegetable oil spray.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Press down with a floured glass.
(Use a paper napkin over the bottom of a glass dipped in flour before pressing.) Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sunshine on a cloud(method:  fireless)
directions: Slice pound cake into 8 portions.
Top each slice with a heaping tablespoonful or two of nondairy whipped topping.
Press a peach half, round side up, into the topping.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat jello and ginger ale until dissolved.
Drain pineapple and use juice to make one cup.
Mix with jello.
Refrigerate until it starts to set.
Add can of pineapple and cranberry sauce. Refrigerate until congealed.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour on top of jello mixture.
Top with pecan halves.

title: frozen strawberry pops
directions: You will also need six (3-ounce) paper cups and six wooden sticks.

title: oatmeal herb bread(bread machine)
directions: Bring all refrigerated ingredients to room temperature by letting them stand on counter about 30 minutes.
Place yeast in bread machine pan according to directions in manual.
In medium bowl, combine flour, oats, cheese, sugar, salt and seasoning; mix well.
In separate bowl, combine buttermilk and oil; mix well. Place dry ingredients and buttermilk mixture in bread machine pan according to manual.
Select white bread and light crust settings. Remove bread from pan to wire rack.
Cool completely before slicing.
Yield:
1 1/2 pound loaf (16 servings).

title: german sweet chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Stir the sugar into melted chocolate and margarine.
Stir in eggs and vanilla until completely mixed.
Mix in flour until well blended.
Stir in nuts, spread in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix well all the ingredients.
Spread on English muffins. Bake in 350° oven about 10 to 15 minutes. Cut into quarters. Makes 24.

title: christmas or southern kisses
directions: Beat whites with cream of tartar until past frothy.
Add sugar (1 tablespoon at a time).
Continue to beat until it loses glossiness.
Add vanilla.
Fold in nut meats.
Drop by tablespoon or less on brown paper or cookie sheet.
Place in 400° oven; close door and immediately turn off oven.
Leave in oven overnight.
Do not open oven door.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat until fluffy.
Add 7-Up and beat well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
While hot, cover with topping.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: jessica's favorite rice pudding
directions: Soak rice in warm water for a few hours or overnight.
Drain and put in a large heavy pot with salt and milk.
Heat, stirring often.
Bring to a boil; reduce and simmer for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Remove rice mixture from heat; stir in egg mixture.
Return to heat until it comes to a slow boil.
As soon as it starts to boil, remove from heat.
Pour into a large bowl; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cool 2 hours, then refrigerate.

title: chinese beets
directions: Mix all in saucepan.
Cook for 3 minutes on medium heat until thickened.
Let cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Cut cabbage in small pieces.
Chop up tomato, cucumber, sweet pepper and onion; add to cabbage.
Add mayonnaise, sugar, salt and black pepper to mix just before you serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray Pam in pie dish. Spread out first pie crust in dish. Open all cans of chicken and spread in dish. Don't drain chicken. Drain Veg-All veggies and put in bowl and pour soup in it, mix together. Sprinkle pinch of salt and pepper on chicken. Pour veggies and soup on chicken, spread. Place second pie crust on top, folding up so mixture won't fall out. Poke holes in top of crust with knife. Cook at 350 degrees for 45 minutes until golden. After cooked, take out of oven and cool for 10 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions and margarine until transparent.
Add corn bread stuffing, sour cream and mushroom soup into casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green beans deluxe(microwave)
directions: In a deep 1 1/2-quart dish, combine beans and soup mix.
Top with onion rings.
Heat, uncovered, on High for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: marinated beets
directions: In a stainless steel pan, mix vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper; boil for 2 minutes.
Peel and thinly slice beets and place in a bowl.
Cover with hot vinegar; allow to cool and refrigerate. Stir every 6 hours.
Prepare at least 12 hours in advance.
Makes 2 cups.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Saute onion in melted butter; stir in flour and salt and pepper.
Add sour cream and heat, but do not boil.
Stir in drained green beans.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese. May double or triple recipe.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: 1-2-3 fudge sauce
directions: Put Carnation, sugar and chocolate in saucepan; cook on low heat.
When sauce begins to boil, cook for 15 minutes.
Stir sauce frequently to prevent it from burning or scorching.
After 15 minutes, remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat with an eggbeater until smooth.
Serve warm or chilled over cake or ice cream.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Wrap cauliflower in plastic wrap.
Cook with stem up in a microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Turn over and cook for 4 minutes more.
Break apart and put in casserole dish.

title: spicy peach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin, sugar and spices with boiling water.
Add syrup and vinegar; chill until it starts to thicken.
Add peaches and refrigerate until firm.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Mix together the margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix instant pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix both mixtures together, then layer cookie crumbs and pudding mixture, starting with cookie crumbs.
Leave enough crumbs for top.

title: chicken casserole(serves 6)
directions: Grease casserole dish; melt margarine in bottom (1/2 stick). Sprinkle rice over bottom of dish.
Mix the 2 cans of soup and only 1 can of water together.
Pour over rice; mix thoroughly. Place breasts on top of rice.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until chicken is tender, rice has absorbed the liquid and the soup has thickened.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in microwave with package intact.
Heat thoroughly.
In a large Dutch oven, combine Cheez Whiz, chopped onion, soup and margarine.
Heat to a boil, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and stir in rice.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes. Stir in broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 375° until brown and bubbly, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: orange loaf cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together into bowl.
Beat all ingredients for 4 minutes.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan and bake 60 to 65 minutes at 350°.
(Cakes of this kind often rise slightly in center and "crack".)

title: herbed leg of lamb
directions: Rub all surfaces of lamb with 1 clove garlic.
Cut this clove and one more into slivers.
Slit skin of lamb at intervals and insert garlic slivers.
Blend next 6 ingredients to a paste. Spread over surface of roast.
Place lamb on a rack, covered, in roasting pan and roast for 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Check with roasting thermometer (150° for medium rare to 175° for well done). Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix
cups
sugar,
shortening, eggs and milk until well blended.
Stir
in 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and
cloves; fold in berries.
Spread batter in greased 9-inch square
pan.
Combine
remaining
ingredients
and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle
crumbs
over
batter.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes
or until cake top springs back when lightly touched. Serve warm, cut into squares, with a lemon sauce.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Mince and blend all ingredients until thoroughly mixed. Spread bread of your choice with mayonnaise, then with mixture. Cut in party shapes.

title: old-fashioned fudge
directions: Butter 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In 3 1/2-quart saucepan mix sugar with dry gelatin.
Add milk, corn syrup, unsweetened chocolate and butter.
Cook, over medium heat and stirring frequently, to 238° on candy thermometer or until a little in cold water forms soft ball that flattens when removed from water.
Remove from heat.
Pur into large mixing bowl.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool 25 minutes.
Beat with wooden spoon until candy thickens.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread in prepared pan.
Let cool, then cut into squares.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar and stir into pudding. Crush cookies up into fairly fine crumbs.
Layer the pudding mixture and then cookies with the cookie mix as the top layer.

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Combine juice, water, sugar and salt in coffee pot.
Place spices in coffee pot basket; perk and serve hot.
Makes 10 cups.

title: italian chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together water, rice, tomatoes, cheese, onion and 1 teaspoon Italian dressing into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and remaining Italian dressing.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out bread dough in rectangular shape.
Spread 4 ounces pizza sauce over dough, staying 1 inch from edges.
Place pepperoni, Canadian bacon and mushrooms over tomato sauce.
Cover these ingredients with cheese (both kinds).
Squeeze 4 tiny dots of mustard on cheese (space evenly).
Starting with one of the longer sides of the rectangle, roll bread into a tube.
Bake according to bread dough directions.
Pour remaining 4 ounces of pizza sauce over finished stromboli (reheat sauce if necessary). Serves 2.

title: easy breakfast rolls
directions: Boil sugars, butter and ice cream together.
Stand biscuits on edge in a Bundt cake pan.
Stack until full.
Pour caramel mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
May add nuts, raisins or cinnamon, if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into balls.
Refrigerate several hours. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: corn muffins
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Put in muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until done.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix and put into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour after it begins to boil.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Combine ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Serve with ice or lime sherbet.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and black pepper.
Pour melted butter into baking dish.
Layer chicken on top of butter.
Bake chicken in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken to coat with butter.
Mix together soups and water.
This should be slightly loose.
More water can be added.
Remove chicken from oven and pour off any grease.
Pour soup over top of chicken.
Lay onion rings on top of chicken and soup mixture. Return to oven and bake 30 minutes longer or until chicken is tender.
Delicious served with rice.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable soup in crock-pot
directions: Sprinkle stew beef with tenderizer.
Place in crock-pot.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Add water.
Place lid on pot and cook on low all night.
Next morning, stir to mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Two hours before serving, add rice.
One hour before serving, add macaroni.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.
The longer it cooks, the better it is!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour.
Bake at 350° until done, 15 minutes to 1 hour.

title: italian vegetable combo
directions: Coat a large skillet with cooking spray; add oil and place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add corn, tomato, basil and pepper.
Stir-fry 1 minute longer or until thoroughly heated.
Stir in bacon bits and cheese. Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil plus pumpkin.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Use 2 greased loaf pans.
Fill half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin tins with liners.
In large bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
Set aside.
Put milk, eggs, sugar, peanut butter, applesauce and salt in small bowl and blend with hand mixer.
Pour over dry ingredients, stirring until moist.
Divide batter.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Place in small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir and pour over cabbage mixture.
Do not stir.
Cover immediately and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Mix well and return to refrigerator until needed.
Keeps well with minimal refrigeration and is excellent for picnics or camping.

title: fluffy omelet
directions: Heat oven to 375° to 400°.
Beat yolks with fork and add to them 1 tablespoon cold milk or hot water for each yolk.
Add salt and pepper.
Beat whites until they adhere to the sides of the bowl and fold them in.
Melt the teaspoon of butter in a medium-size heavy pan which can go into the oven.
When the pan is hot, pour the eggs in and brown on top of the stove for less than a minute; then put in oven for 15 minutes.
Do not open the oven door while cooking.
Test with a knife.
If it is finished, it will be firm.
Make 2 nicks on opposite sides and fold.

title: donuts
directions: Beat well.
Add enough flour to roll out.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, melted butter and 3 tablespoons sugar; press into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: apple fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, cut apples into bite size pieces.
Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges, and mix with apples.
Add pie filling and mix with the fruit mixture.
Refrigerate.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: beef stew with lima beans
directions: Brown meat and saute onions in cooking pot over medium heat. Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, cinnamon stick and lima beans.
Cover; bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: three cheese chicken
directions: Flatten chicken as much as possible.
Make a paste of 3 cheeses.
Put in center of chicken; wrap chicken around cheese. Secure with toothpick.
Dip in egg and milk, then in bread crumbs. Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in food processor; add lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
In a separate bowl combine and blend sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning mix.
Spread 2 cans jalapeno bean dip onto bottom of 8 x 12-inch glass cake pan.
Top with avocado mix, then sour cream mix.
Cover with onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Chill; serve with tortilla chips.

title: apple dapple
directions: Mix together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and add to the oil/sugar mixture. Fold in nuts and apple. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: batter franks
directions: Mix together in order given and dip wieners into batter.
Fry in deep fat until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with mustard and catsup.

title: lentil soup
directions: Fry first 5 ingredients. Add lentils and fry one more minute. Cover all with water. Slow cook for 45 minutes.

title: mixed greens with honey raspberry vinaigrette
directions: Combine vinegar and honey in small bowl; mix well.
To serve, drizzle 2 to 3 tablespoons vinegar honey mixture, oil and oregano over lettuce greens.
Toss to coat.
Garnish with fruit if desired.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Chop or blend dried beef to small pieces.
Chop onion.
Add all ingredients, reserving 1/4 of beef for garnish.
Mix well.
Form into ball.
Roll in remaining beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: de lux potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in large casserole.
Sprinkle with green pepper.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Last 15 minutes of baking sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over top.
Delicious!

title: almond vegetables mandarin
directions: Cook and stir in skillet over medium high heat the carrots and green beans in salad oil for 2 minutes.
Add cauliflower and green onions; cook 1 minute.
Add water, chicken stock base, cornstarch and garlic powder.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Vegetables should be crisp-tender.
If they need further cooking, reduce heat, cover and steam to desired doneness.
Add almonds.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bundt cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and set aside.
In separate bowl mix sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Spread 1/2 cinnamon mixture in bottom of greased and floured pan.
Add 1/2 batter.
Add rest of cinnamon mixture, then add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Grease and flour pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: kahlua(makes 3 quarts)
directions: Boil 4 cups water and add 4 cups sugar to make a simple syrup. Let boil a few more minutes.
Add instant coffee and shut off heat and let cool, add vodka.
Cut vanilla beans in half the long way.
Put in each bottle, divide solution into 3 equal parts. Stir well, then fill bottles.
Let stand in a cool, dark place for at least 10 days before using.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan; dump pineapple and pie filling in. Slightly mix.
Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix on top.
Slice margarine and dot over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Boil sugar and water to spin thread (come off spoon in thread when you spin spoon).
Add salt to mix and a little cinnamon or almond flavoring.
Remove from heat and pour nuts into mixture. Stir until crystallized.

title: glazed donuts
directions: Scald milk.
Add margarine, salt and sugar.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Beat eggs; add milk and yeast.
Stir in flour until not sticky.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise again until double in bulk. Drop into hot cooking oil, then turn and brown on other side. Drain on paper towels.
Dip in glaze.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
If batter seems too thick, add a little more milk.
Heat and grease pan.
Pour batter about 3 inches around.
Turn when bubbly. When done, put butter on it.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add onion, green pepper and celery and saute until vegetables are soft.
Add tomatoes, puree, spices, sugar, wine and shrimp.
(Shrimp cooked in shells have extra flavor from a thin layer of fat between shells and the meat.) Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Makes about 8 cups.
Can be served over rice.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: strawberry jam cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add
jam.
Beat well.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add flour, salt and spices alternately with milk, beating vigorously after each addition.
Line two 9-inch pans, greased, with a round of waxed paper.
Lightly flour.
Pour batter into pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Ice with Caramel Frosting.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Place butter, water and cocoa into a pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Mix flour, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Pour cocoa mixture into dry ingredients and mix with a fork.
Beat eggs and sour cream.
Add baking soda.
Mix altogether.
Pour into greased 17 1/2 x 11-inch sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add soups, Ro-Tel and chili powder. Soak tortillas in chicken broth.
Line casserole dish with softened tortillas.
Layer chicken, sauce and cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Into
2 quart baking dish (spray with Pam).
Layer half the beans,
chestnuts
and
onion.
Cover
with half of soup, salt, pepper and cheese.
Repeat the layers; top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cut large shrimp in half.
Blend flour into oil and brown, stirring constantly.
Add water gradually and cook until thick, smooth and shining.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: mock red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the above ingredients.
Pour into greased cake pans.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Slice French bread in half lengthwise.
Mix thoroughly the last 3 ingredients.
Spread on bread.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on each half loaf.
Put on lower oven rack and broil until cheese is melted.

title: crazy cake
directions: Place sifter in a baking dish and then sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda.
Make 3 holes in the dry ingredients.
In these, put the oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Over these, pour the cold water and stir with a fork until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: one egg cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the shortening and sugar together. Add the rest of the ingredients. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Great with fresh strawberries.

title: banana nut bread
directions: *May use self-rising flour and omit salt, soda and baking powder.

title: butterscotch cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine over hot (not boiling) water, butterscotch morsels and butter.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to large bowl.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and walnuts with a fork until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Take about 20 Ritz crackers, crushed and add melted butter.
Spread on top of casserole and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: cheesy beef taco dip
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef, onion and green pepper over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in the cheeses, taco sauce, tomatoes, mushrooms and olives. Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: mom's barbecue sauce
directions: In small bowl, beat egg well. Add oil and beat until well blended. Add remaining ingredients and stir.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding real good.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Add orange Tang.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add one egg at a time.
Add bananas and mix well.
Add flour and soda, alternately with milk and beat well.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Bake in layers.
Put together with favorite icing.

title: simple and easy sticky buns
directions: Rub frozen dough with shortening and let rise according to package directions.
Sprinkle flour on rolling pin and board. Roll dough out as far as possible (not too thin), forming a rectangle.
Spread butter on dough, covering completely.
Sprinkle brown sugar, white sugar, cinnamon and nuts (optional), covering dough evenly.
Roll dough up, forming a long roll.
Cut into 2-inch long pieces.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar and warm water together to cover bottom of 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Place sticky buns in cake pan in syrup.
Let rise 1 to 2 hours.
Mix additional 1/2 cup brown sugar and warm water and pour over top of sticky buns.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour or until tops are slightly brown.
Don't overdo.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Heat chocolate and shortening in 2-quart saucepan over low heat until melted; remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan, for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: amish cream pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together granulated sugar, cornstarch and salt. Whisk in the half and half or cream and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter, brown sugar and vanilla till butter melts.
Pour into baked pie shell and sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.

title: marsha's sweet soup
directions: Cook and drain first 3 ingredients.
In a large pot, add tomato sauce, tomato paste and water.
Drain and add peas, carrots and chili beans (corn can be used, also).
Then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, on low heat for 30 minutes.
It sticks easily.
If mixture is too thick, add a little water.

title: tiny meatballs
directions: Mix well and form into balls, about the size of a penny.
Fry until lightly brown.

title: easy quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Layer bacon, onion and cheese in pan. Combine milk, eggs, Bisquick baking mix, salt and seasonings in mixture.
Mix at high speed for 1 minute.
Carefully pour egg mixture evenly over layered ingredients in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine sauce ingredients and pour over the chops.
Cover with heavy-duty foil and bake at 400° for one hour.

title: corrine's cole slaw dressing
directions: Blend together and pour over cole slaw.
Let sit for a while before serving.

title: christine's bread pudding
directions: Mix ingredients (except cinnamon and raisins) in blender until well blended.
Butter or margarine 4 to 5 slices of bread.
Break or cut into small pieces.
Put bread and milk mixture and raisins, if desired, into bowl.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake in pan of water for about 1 hour at 400° until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix first four ingredients with a hand beater just until smooth.
pour 1/2 c. hot beef roast drippings in a 9 by 9 square pan.
Pour batter into this pan.
Bake at 425 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve with beef roast and vegetables.

title: porcupines
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients except tomato soup and sugar.
Form into small meatballs and place in baking dish.
Stir sugar into tomato soup. Do not dilute soup.
Cover each meatball with 1 tablespoon of undiluted soup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover for 30 minutes while baking and uncover during the last 30 minutes of baking time.

title: crab pate
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese together.
In bowl mix remaining ingredients.
Add soup and cream cheese.
Pour in oiled mold. Chill for 6 hours or overnight.

title: sherry's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ground beef and ground chuck with egg.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Place in baking dish and coat top of loaf with ketchup.
Cook about 25 minutes or until well done.
Drain off excess oil; let cool and slice and serve.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mash yolks very fine, then add rest of ingredients.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

Sift together flour and soda. Add to butter mixture, a little at a time, blending well after each addition. Stir in sour cream and mashed bananas. Fold in nuts. Pour in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pink stuff
directions: In a large bowl, mix the cherry pie filling, drained pineapple and oranges.
Cut banana up and mix well.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Serve chilled.

title: bite-size party pizza
directions: Brown sausage and ground meat.
Add Velveeta and seasonings to you taste.
Spread on party rye bread.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: hot crabmeat dip(appetizers)
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend together cream cheese, half and half cream, crabmeat, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soup and water together.
Spread rice in casserole dish. Layer chicken on top of rice.
Pour chicken soup over chicken and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill until set.

title: pesto vegetables
directions: Cut each potato into 8 wedges.
In large saucepan, cover potatoes with salted water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add onions and green beans; boil 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain; place in bowl.
Add pesto, salt and pepper; too. Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: zucchini cheese casserole
directions: Add rice, onion and 1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup rapidly boiling water.
Cover tightly; boil gently for 20 minutes.
Bring 1/2 cup water to boil.
Cook squash until tender, about 8 minutes (or steam).
Drain.
Gently mix rice, squash, tomato sauce and green pepper.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake uncovered about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab rice soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan; add onion, green pepper and celery.
Saute until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients except shrimp and crab meat.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 30 minutes until rice is tender.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into meatballs (use tablespoon of measuring spoons).
Chill.
Brown slowly, draining grease.
Put about 16 meatballs in frypan at a time.
Cook slowly with cover at about 200°.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake the brownie mix ahead in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool. Crumble 1/2 of the brownies in the bottom of bowl.
Prepare Jell-O chocolate mousse as directed and pour 1/2 of mixture on top of brownies.
Spread 1/2 of Cool Whip on mousse.
Crumble Heath bars plus chopped pecans and sprinkle 1/2 of the Heath bars mixture on the Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers one more time: brownies, mousse, Cool Whip and Heath bars.
Let set overnight.
Enjoy!!
Serves 15 to 20.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Melt butter in dutch oven, stir in flour.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Add milk, stirring constantly until thick.
Add potatoes and onions.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat, simmer for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until cheese is melted.
8 - 10 servings.

title: b l t's to go
directions: Cover 1 slice of bread with lettuce leaves.
Cover lettuce with mayonnaise.
Place tomato slices under running water to wash out seeds and place on top of mayonnaise.
Crumble bacon over tomato slices.
Cover bacon with more lettuce leaves and top with another slice of bread.
Do not cut.
By washing out seeds and putting the mayonnaise between lettuce leaves, bread will not become soggy.
Crumbled bacon will assure bacon flavor in every bite.

title: banana bread(aunt mamie's)
directions: Use mixer to cream the butter (margarine) and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, vanilla and bananas.
Bake 30 minutes at 325° in a greased and floured 8 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked haddock
directions: Arrange fish on bottom of a flat greased baking dish.
Mix milk into soup; spoon soup over fish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes until fillets are tender.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with parsley.

title: yellow-stone applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Sift together flour and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend 2 teaspoons vanilla into applesauce.
Add soda, then blend with batter.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.
Before baking, sprinkle tops with cinnamon sugar.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and place in baking dish.

title: pecan clusters
directions: In a large bowl, mix together butter, dark brown sugar, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and top with 10x sugar.
Makes about 18.

title: finney's potato salad
directions: Cube and boil potatoes.
Drain.
Add mayo.
Whip with mixer until smooth.
Add onion, bell pepper, pimento and mustard.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients together, cut in shortening with pastry blender
or
knives.
Dissolve
yeast
in
warm
water (temperature
according
to
type
of yeast used) and add with buttermilk
to
dry
ingredients.
Mix
well.
Knead a little, adding
flour if dough seems sticky, until dough forms a ball. Roll out
and
cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes
or
until done.
This biscuit dough can be made ahead and kept
in the refrigerator in a covered plastic bowl.
Use as much as you need at a time.
Cut biscuits can be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen, just put them on the pan and bake when you are
ready for them.
Dough can also be used to make small dumplings
for
soups
and stews.
