Rolled out thin, the dough is a good crust for meat pies.
A real angel to have on hand!

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put sugar, butter, milk and salt in large heavy pan.
Bring to rolling boil for 9 minutes.
Take off heat and add chocolate bits, bars, marshmallow cream and nuts (one item at a time).
Stir continually until mixture starts to set up.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Cool; cover and store in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heavily grease a large loaf pan.
In a mixer bowl, cream shortening and sugar thoroughly with a mixer. Add eggs and bananas.
In another bowl, combine all the dry ingredients and blend well, then add to the banana mixture.
Mix well.
If a little thick, add milk.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted in top comes out clean.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: mashed potato cakes
directions: Mix potatoes and slightly beaten egg together.
Season to taste.
Shape into round flat cakes about 3/4-inch thick.
Melt enough Crisco into heavy frying pan to cover the bottom well. When hot, put cake in and brown on one side.
Turn with spatula and brown cakes on the other side.

title: impressive lemon pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar, adding sugar gradually. Nest into greased deep pie pan.
Cook by either of 2 methods: Heat oven to 425° and then turn off.
Leave in overnight.
Or bake 20 minutes at 275°, then 40 minutes at 300°.
Cool.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Cut up all solid ingredients as fine as possible and mix well with mayonnaise.
Roll in long roll, size of Ritz crackers.
Store in the refrigerator, wrapped until ready to use.

title: broccoli, chicken and rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in boiling water; drain.
Saute cut up chicken, onion and celery in margarine in skillet.
Add soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Put rice, broccoli and rest of ingredients into a casserole dish.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry & caramel date bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl combine cranberries and 2 Tbsp. sugar. In another bowl combine 2 c. flour, oats, remaining 1/2 c. sugar, brown sugar and soda. Add oleo, mix well.
Reserve 1 c. crumb mixture. Press remainder firmly on bottom of 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle dates, nuts and cranberry mixture over crust.
Mix caramel topping and remaining 1/3 c. flour, spoon over fruit and nuts. Top with reserved crumb mixture. Bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool, cut into bars.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter.
Beat together. Add 2 eggs, flour and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Set aside.
Put brownie mix, chocolate package, 2 tablespoons water and 3 eggs in bowl.
Mix about 50 strokes by hand.
Pour half into 13 x 9-inch pan (greased).
Pour all of the cheese mix over brownies. Spoon remaining brownie layer here and there over the cream cheese mix. Pull knife through batter to create swirls.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool and frost with easy milk chocolate frosting or leave as is and enjoy.

title: hearty beef and barley soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine barley and enough water to cover. Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
In a large kettle or soup pot, heat oil over high heat.
Brown meat, chopping into small bits.
Add onion and garlic; saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cooked barley, 9 cups hot water, bouillon cubes, Worcestershire sauce, basil, salt and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes longer.
(Vary the cooking time so that vegetables get thoroughly done.)
Yields 3 quarts.
A bit of macaroni or spaghetti may be added, if desired.

title: rice consomm
directions: Place all ingredients except butter in a casserole. Mix well and arrange slices of butter over the top. Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ginger fruit crisp
directions: In plastic bag, finely crush cookies.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine and remove from heat.
Blend in crumbs, nuts and brown sugar.
Arrange fruit in a lightly greased, 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Serves approximately 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except ketchup.
Bake until almost done at 400° for about 1 hour, then top with ketchup and finish baking.
Slice into squares.

title: egg custard
directions: Blend all ingredients together approximately 5 seconds.
Pour into buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Add coconut if you like.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Combine concentrates, pineapple juice, water and salt in large container.
Stir well.
Chill.
Stir in club soda before serving.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, peppers and garlic.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine tomatoes, Prego, hamburger, onions, pepper, salt, pepper, garlic and macaroni.
Mix well.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta. Mix with broccoli, peppers and dressing. You may substitute pimientos for red peppers. Add cheese, tomatoes or croutons if you like. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish, skin side up, in a single layer.
In bowl, mix together the salad dressing, soup mix and preserves; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven, basting occasionally, for about 1 hour, or until chicken is tender.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken when serving.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Fry rounded tablespoons in hot oil.

title: pineapple-barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces side by side in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Mix barbecue sauce, brown sugar and pineapple together and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 350°, basting often.
If it begins to brown, cover with aluminum foil.

title: potato hot dish
directions: Put one layer of potatoes, 1 layer cream of mushroom soup, 1 layer of vegetable soup, 1 layer hamburger.
Keep putting in layers until all is used.
Add 3/4 to 1 can of milk over the top. Bake 2 to 3 hours at 350°.

title: citrus and mango salad(makes 2 to 4 servings)
directions: *Amount needed for each serving.

title: sheep-wagon carrot cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in medium saucepan.
Simmer for 5 minutes, then cover and let rest for 12 hours.

title: potato refrigerator dough
directions: Proof yeast by pouring yeast in 1/2 cup of the warm water with 1 teaspoon of the sugar.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together along with 1/2 the flour.
Add yeast mixture.
Continue to add remaining flour.
Knead dough 6 to 10 minutes on a floured surface.
Place in a greased mixing bowl; cover.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours before using.
Can keep dough at least 1 week, taking off amounts you wish to use.
Shape rolls or bread and place in a warm place to double in size.
Bake at 350° to 375°.

title: neiman-marcus cake bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Pat into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until light brown on top.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: mango ginger parfaits
directions: Directions to Make Mango Ice Cream:
Soften vanilla ice cream. Add mango puree and cumquat juice.
Place in mold and freeze 2 hours.
Unmold and place in blender and add ginger.
Return to mold and refreeze.

title: marble cookies
directions: Mix 1 stick of butter, egg and chocolate cake mix.
Mix 1 stick of butter, 1 egg and other cake mix in separate bowl. Spoon a little of each mix together on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in saucepan over moderate heat 5 minutes until limp. Add potatoes, chicken broth, salt and celery salt. Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until potatoes are nearly tender. Add milk and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 3 to 5 minutes until potatoes are done.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients in a medium bowl, cutting flour, baking powder and salt into Crisco, then adding milk.
Mix lightly (using your clean hands for best results).
Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake at 450° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 12.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain juice off of oranges.
Bring juice to boil and dissolve jello.
Add oranges and crushed pineapple.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and chill overnight.
Next morning, whip the Cool Whip and mayonnaise to top jello.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: easy cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crusts. Makes 2 pies.

title: orange julius
directions: Put in blender and blend well.

title: cherry nut salad
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, mix gelatin and water until dissolved.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Stir and mix well.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Do not overbeat.
Spread on top of gelatin mixture and sprinkle with nuts.

title: diabetic snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
In saucepan, put 1 cup orange juice, Sweet One and lemon juice.
Bring to a rolling boil. Add gelatine mixture and remove from heat, add remaining orange juice.
Chill until thickened like jelly.
Beat with mixer and add 3/4 container of Cool Whip.
Line bowl with waxed paper.
Break cake into small pieces.
Alternate layers with cake and gelatine mixture.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and frost with remaining Cool Whip.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Debone chicken and cut up. Place chicken in 12 x 9-inch pan or dish. Mix broth and soup and pour over chicken. For crust, mix flour, milk and margarine. Pour over chicken. Do not stir or mix. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until crust is golden brown.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken soup

title: barbecue chicken pizza
directions: Spread barbecue sauce on shells.
Add chicken, green onions, bean sprouts, red pepper and cheese.
Bake according to shell directions.
Serves 8.

title: homemade mustard
directions: Mix vinegar and mustard; set overnight.
Mix with eggs, sugar and salt.
Cook 15 minutes until thick in top of a double boiler. Save baby food jars or any small jar with tight fitting lid. Mustard is kept nicely in refrigerator for weeks.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt the bars of chocolate. Stir in 1/2 tub of Cool Whip. Mix until light brown. Pour into pie crust. Put rest of Cool Whip on top. Chill for 2 hours or longer. Serves 4.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Crumble sausage and cook.
Mix cornmeal, flour and sugar.
Add chopped jalapenos and cheese; mix.
Add eggs, milk and sausage. Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° until brown.

title: german pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Add Crisco and mix with fingers until of mealy consistency.
Beat egg in cup and add water to measure 1 cup.
Add mixture and combine until moistened. Roll out baseball size portion of dough on floured board to make 1 crust.

title: breakfast cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries until soft. To this add the pineapple and sugar. Serve this warm over toast.

title: white bread
directions: Grease two 8 x 4 or 4 x 5 inch loaf pans.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
In large bowl combine 2 c. flour, sugar, salt and yeast, blend well.
In a small saucepan heat oil and water until very warm.
Add warm liquid to flour mixture and blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in 2 1/2 to 3 c. flour until dough comes away from the sides of bowl.

title: sherley's tomatoes(4 servings)
directions: Mix cheese, green onions, parsley and mayonnaise.
Core and cut tomatoes in half horizontally.
Put tomatoes, cut side up, in shallow baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, green chilies, sour cream and cumin in saucepan.
Heat just to boiling, then reduce heat to low.
Soften tortillas by heating about 1/2-inch of oil in a skillet over medium heat.
When hot, dip tortilla in oil briefly, about 2 seconds per side.
Remove to a paper towel lined plate.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix meat, soup and sour cream in pan; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese and serve.

title: dill dip
directions: *Use equal amounts of each.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Bring to boil first 5 ingredients.
Reduce heat; stir in oleo until thick.
Pour over cooked carrots.

title: french onion soup
directions: Brown onions in butter. Add consomme, pepper, thyme, salt and water. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: easy barbecued pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops in a single layer in a shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover chops with catsup and pour cola over all ingredients.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cool potatoes.
Peel and cube.
Place in a 12 x 12-inch casserole.
Grate onion and spread over potatoes.
Mix sour cream, chicken broth, half and half cream, salt, pepper and margarine in a saucepan.
Heat and mix well.
Pour over potatoes and onion in casserole.
Spread one 8 ounce package Cheddar cheese over casserole.
Mix 1/4 cup margarine and 3/4 cup crushed cornflakes. Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cheesy potato puff
directions: Add process cheese spread, egg yolks, pimiento and parsley to potatoes; mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
When cake is done, prick holes in cake.
Let cake cool.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Keep refrigerated. Should set for a couple of hours before serving.

title: deer jerky(recipe for 2 or 3 pounds of deer meat.)
directions: Marinate for 24 hours at room temperature. Bake in oven on low heat until done.

title: blueberry refrigerated pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and milk in a medium saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until mixture thickens to custard.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: quick chocolate eclairs
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Add whipped topping and blend.
Layer a 9 x 12-inch pan with graham crackers and pudding mix.
Cover with cake frosting.
(Frosting works best if heated in microwave so it can be poured on in a thin layer.)

title: louisiana corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook first five ingredients together until beef is browned.
Mix together.
Grease 9 x 11-inch dish. Spread 1/2 of cornmeal mixture into dish.
Add meat mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Spread the rest of cornmeal batter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until corn bread is browned and done in center.
Serve with green vegetable or salad and your meal is complete.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Pare cucumbers and remove seeds, also the peppers and onions, then grind all together.
Add salt and allow to stand for 3 hours. Drain and cook in the vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Just before removing from heat, add turmeric.
Seal in jars.

title: con queso-cheese dip
directions: In a crock-pot:
Cut cheese up in blocks and melt.
Brown sausage or hamburger and onion then drain.
Dump salsa and meat in with cheese and mix all together.
Stir occasionally until all cheese is melted.
If dip is thick, then add a little milk.
Serve with tortilla chips as dip or over baked potatoes.

title: double chocolate treasures
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt 1 cup chocolate chips. Stir until smooth.
Cool slightly.
Beat together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Combine and then add dry ingredients except powdered sugar.
Stir in the remaining chocolate chips.
Cool in the refrigerator for easier handling, then shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Let cool. Cool 1 minute before removing.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil butter, cocoa, sugar and milk for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and salt; beat well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool and serve.

title: cape cod oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir in Egg with Sugar, Butter, Shortening, Molasses, and Milk. Add Oatmeal and Raisins or Nuts.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and combine with egg mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookies sheet.
Bake at 350 for 12 minutes.

title: lime honey salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; beat with a rotary beater or shake thoroughly.
Chill before serving with any fresh or canned fruit salad.
This mixture will remain emulsified much longer than many other dressings, but should be shaken up or beaten just before serving.

title: cinnamon jumbles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift and stir flour, soda and salt, then add to mixture and mix well.

title: velvet drinking dessert
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend 10 seconds.
Pour into sherbet glasses.

title: sunday night tamale pie
directions: In large, heavy frying pan, put olive oil and butter.
Melt; turn burner off.
Chop up onion and mince garlic; add to pan. Cook slowly, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes.
Then add your ground round.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
While still cooking, add packed tomatoes and break up the big pieces with spoon.
Add cream-style corn, mushrooms (including liquid), chili sauce and chopped ripe olives.
Then add salt.
Now, add cornmeal, sifting it in slowly with a big spoon, and stirring as you add.
Add half of grated cheese (1/4 cup), stirring it thoroughly.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in medium saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in cake mix. Mix well, then pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch morsels and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onions and mushrooms in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Spread rolls over hot casserole to make a crust.
Top with butter and cheese.
Bake 5 or 10 minutes or more until golden brown.

title: camp slomgoo
directions: Brown ground beef, saute celery and onion in large pot.
Add soups, Chinese vegetables and chestnuts.
Cook peas in small amount of water; drain and add.
Season with salt and pepper and add a little Worcestershire sauce, if desired.

title: italian soupa
directions: Saute sausage.
Remove excess drippings and sausage.
Fry green peppers and onion.
Add sausage, wine and broth.
Boil until wine smell is gone (about 15 minutes).
Add seasonings, tomatoes and dry noodles.
Simmer 1 hour.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve cranberry sauce in hot jello.
When well dissolved, add crushed pineapple.
Place in 9 x 13-inch glass Pyrex dish when cooled and place in refrigerator to set.

title: scalloped potatoes with franks
directions: Place 2 cups of sliced potatoes in a 2-quart greased casserole.
Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Sprinkle 1/2 over potatoes.
Add 1/2 of the onion, butter and frankfurters. Repeat in same order.
Add milk.
Bake in a 350° oven for an hour, or until done.

title: thick strawberry milk shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend at high speed until smooth or for 1 minute.
Serve immediately.
If using fresh strawberries, add 3 ice cubes to make thicker shake.
Makes approximately 1 (12 ounce) serving.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 fruit and 1/2 nonfat milk.

title: cucumber salad with sour cream
directions: Two hours before serving, sprinkle it with salt.
Drain this brine when ready to make the salad.
Add parsley (cut fine), garlic (cut very fine), 1 sliced onion, 1 salad spoon of vinegar, 1 salad spoon of salad oil, 2 spoons of thick sour cream and then more salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix crackers, butter, powdered sugar and peanut butter (with hands is easier).
Pat down in large cake pan.
Spread melted chocolate chips on top.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: vegen-stroganoff
directions: Drain and reserve liquid from Vegecuts and mushrooms.
Cut Vegecuts into thin strips and dry out on cookie sheet in low oven. Place in heavy skillet and fry in hot oil until brown.
Add remaining ingredients, including liquid from cans.
Simmer slowly for about 25 minutes.
Add sour cream before serving.
Serve with hot rice or noodles.

title: great pork chops
directions: Coat chops in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown chops on both sides in hot shortening.
Place in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.

title: dutch sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugar and butter together until creamed.
Add flour, two tablespoons at a time.
When blended, add water in which baking soda and vanilla have been dissolved.
Form dough into a roll and wrap with waxed paper.
Place in the refrigerator overnight or for 6 to 8 hours.
When dough is solid, cut into 1/4-inch slices. Place on ungreased cookie sheet an inch apart and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line oblong cake pan with graham crackers; mix pudding with milk according to package directions.
Add Cool Whip to pudding. Mix well.
Pour 1/2 mixture on graham crackers.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.
Pour remaining mixture on top of crackers.
Top graham crackers with chocolate frosting. Refrigerate overnight.

title: rotel tomato-cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in saucepan, being careful not to scorch.
Cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Add to cheese.
Heat, stirring constantly.
Good as chip dip or poured over tortilla chips.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spread potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let thaw.
Mix other ingredients together; pour over potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion and A.1. until of spreading consistency.
Carefully separate meat into slices and spread with cream cheese mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll; chill.
Just before serving, slice into bite size pieces.

title: punch bowl turtle cake
directions: Cool cake after baking.
Pull cake apart into small chunks. Spread in a bottom layer of bowl.
Pour caramel sauce generously over cake.
Sprinkle crushed nuts over sauce.
Spread Cool Whip over that.
Repeat with chocolate cake, caramel, nuts and Cool Whip until it reaches the top of the bowl.
(Sometimes I add crushed Oreos or Heath Bar bits.)

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute until soft the onions, celery and carrots.
Add mustard. Warm chicken broth and add to mixture.
Stir in American cheese that has been tossed with flour.
Stir until thick.
Before serving, add can of beer and Polish sausage.
Heat and serve.

title: angel food bars
directions: Mix the 3 ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Top with 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1/2 cup toasted coconut.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a 2-quart casserole.
Cook cabbage in salted, boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain and cool, then chop finely.
In a bowl, blend eggs, butter, cream, salt, pepper and onion powder.
Stir in cabbage.
Put mixture into casserole.
Mix remaining butter and bread crumbs and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 2 cups graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick oleo.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and pat down firmly.

title: glazed carrots(low-fat)
directions: Peel and cut up carrots.
Place in medium size saucepan or one large enough to have only one layer of carrots.
Sprinkle onion and salt over carrots.
Add enough water to saucepan to barely cover the carrots.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Turn to medium-low and continue cooking, uncovered, until carrots are tender and most of the water has evaporated.
Combine melted margarine and lemon juice and pour evenly over carrots.
Continue cooking until liquid is reduced to a buttery glaze.
Yummy!

title: beth's bears
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, shortening, eggs, nutmeg, salt and 2 cups of flour.
Beat on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping occasionally, 2 minutes.
Stir in rest of flour until smooth.
Cover, let rise in warm place until double (about 45 minutes).
Dough is ready when indentation remains when touched with floured finger.
Stir dough down by beating 25 strokes to 1/2 size.
Roll dough into sizes to form body, head and ears.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas.
Pour into well-greased and floured pans.
(I use Baker's Joy.)
Bake in 4 small loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry and drain bacon.
Fry onion in butter.
Add bacon, milk, corn, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes.

title: diet pineapple muffins
directions: Beat egg in a small bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into 3 non-stick muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Break up cake and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix ice cream or yogurt with milk and vanilla pudding.
Pour over cake.
Chill. Mix strawberry Jell-O, water and berries.
Allow to thicken.
Pour over cake and chill.

title: pear relish
directions: Peel and core pears.
Grind pears, onions and peppers.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt, spices and turmeric.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Remove spice bag.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: casserole cheese bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour warm water into a large, warm bowl and sprinkle in yeast.
Stir to dissolve.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, grated cheese and flour.
Stir 2 minutes or until well blended.
Cover.

title: chicken breasts with asparagus
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove, set aside and spoon off fat.
In skillet, combine soup, milk and pepper and stir in asparagus.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet and cover. Cook over low heat 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and asparagus is crisp-tender, stirring often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: festive sweet potato combo
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease 2-quart shallow baking dish. Layer sweet potatoes, 2/3 cup French fried onions and half of the apples. Put wedges in prepared baking dish. Stir together pineapple with juice, sugar and cinnamon in medium bowl. Spoon pineapple mixture over sweet potato mixture. Arrange remaining apple wedges over pineapple layer. Cook. Bake 35 minutes or until heated through. Uncover. Sprinkle with remaining 2/3 cup onions. Bake 3 minutes or until onions are golden. Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Whip cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Combine with strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish and freeze.
Cut in squares.
Can be served on leaf lettuce or by itself.

title: chocolate jello pie
directions: Prepare instant pie filling mixes as directed on package for pie using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: congo squares
directions: Combine brown sugar and melted margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to other mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked chicken tortilla
directions: Wrap chicken in foil and bake 1 hour in 450° oven.
Cut into chunks.

Butter Pyrex dish and pour chicken juice into it.	Cut tortillas into 1-inch strips and layer on the bottom of the dish. Mix soups, milk, salsa, onion and olives together.	Layer the chicken pieces on top of tortilla strips and pour 1/2 soup mixture on top of them.
Repeat the layers and cover with cheese. Refrigerate 12 to 18 hours.
Bake in slow 300° oven for 90 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, stir in spaghetti sauce and heat.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Into the spaghetti, stir margarine, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Form into a crust in a greased baking dish. Spread with cottage cheese, then with ground beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes in round 8-inch pans. It takes longer for larger pans.
A very moist cake.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut egg, remove yolk.
Mix yolks with mayonnaise.
Add vinegar, relish, sugar and mustard.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put egg yolk mixture back into half egg whites. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: duchess potatoes
directions: Combine the mashed potatoes, butter and salt with beaten egg yolks and form into balls, hearts or other shapes (a pastry bag may be used). Place in a greased baking dish and brush over with beaten egg whites. Brown in a hot oven. Serves 4 to 6.

title: almond cookies
directions: Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly golden brown.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix 1/2 cup soup, hamburger, oats, egg, onion and soy sauce.
In 9 x 12-inch pan, firmly shape meat into loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove meat loaf to platter.
Save 3 tablespoons drippings and place in saucepan.
Stir in remaining soup and water.
Heat and serve with meat loaf.
Makes 8 servings.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar in a saucepan; heat to boiling.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Pan may be lined with foil rather than buttered.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: You will need one 9-inch pie pan.

title: egg batter fried fish(pesce di fritta)
directions: Wash fish and drain
in
colander.
Put
oil
in medium non-stick skillet to heat.
Place
fish
in
flour
until well coated and then into eggs mixed with salt and pepper.
Immediately place in hot oil
and
cook
on
medium-high
heat until lightly golden on each side.
Turn
carefully
as not to break fillets. Serve on warm plate with lemon wedges.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Peel and cook zucchini in small amount of water until tender. Put in blender until smooth.
Measure 3 cups zucchini into large kettle.
Add 1/4 cup of lemon juice and Sure-Jell.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add sugar and apricot Jell-O.
Stir well and boil for another 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and put into jars.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter flavored shortening with sugar, egg and vanilla in a bowl at high speed until fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder, ginger and salt in small bowl.
Divide dough in half. Shape into 2 balls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill approximately 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll dough out on lightly floured board.
Roll out 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter any shapes.
Sprinkle with colored sprinkles, if desired.
Bake for 7 minutes or until gold.
Remove and cool.
Great for holidays!

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut flank steak slantwise into 1/8-inch thick slivers and brown in oil in a large frying pan.
Season with salt and pepper. Add onions, garlic, green peppers, celery and bouillon cube. Cover pan tightly and cook over moderate heat until meat and vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cucumber salad
directions: Combine lemon juice or vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in a bowl; mix well.
Add cucumbers.
Sprinkle with chopped dill. Cover and chill for 3 hours or longer.

title: crusty breadsticks
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water in
medium bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add oil and salt.
Stir in enough flour to make smooth dough.
Place on lightly floured surface.
Knead 5 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Roll into 14 x 9-inch rectangle.
Cut into 24 strips.
Twist each strip into an 8-inch rope.
Place 1-inch apart on greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 20 minutes.

title: angel cornsticks
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
In bowl, put eggs, buttermilk and vegetable oil.
Beat well.
Add liquid mixture to meal mix. Stir until batter is smooth.
Bake in preheated hot, well greased cornstick pans at 450°.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Mix with mayonnaise and potatoes.
Sprinkle Bac*Os on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Add yeast to water, stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, margarine or butter and salt; stir in flour.
Roll out on floured board 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into 2 or 3 inch squares.
Dip in melted margarine that has been cooled slightly.
Layer in tube pan staggering pieces.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: cocoa bread pudding
directions: Mix sugar with cocoa, salt and vanilla.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Bake for about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar, shrimp and vinegar together.
Add remaining ingredients (can add any other vegetable you like).

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in large kettle.
Add onion; cook for 3 minutes. Add broccoli and broth; season to taste.
Cover; simmer mixture for 30 minutes.
Puree in batches unless you like it chunky.
Add cream and heat soup over low heat until hot (don't boil).

title: old-fashioned pickled beets
directions: A day or so ahead, arrange beets in a bowl.
Pour on liquid with other ingredients.

title: quick wine cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix with electric beater about 5 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into a greased angel food cake pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan about 5 minutes before turning out on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
